<HEAD>
<TITLE>The New Desktop Projector 5600!</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_products.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/new_products_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "New Products"></A>
<p>
<H2><font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Offers True SVGA Polysilicon Projector</H2>
<H3>Lightweight Desktop Projector 5600 Leads the Industry in Brightness</H3>
</center>

<A HREF="jpgs/proj5600.jpg"><IMG SRC="gifs/proj5600.gif" border = none align = right width = 288 height = 215></A>
<font size = "+2"><B>Y</B></font><font size = "+1">ou get true SVGA resolution and superior brightness in the lightweight Desktop Projector 5600.
<p>
The <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font><sup>&#174;</sup> <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP5600&sction=Description">Desktop Projector  5600</A> offers what many presenters have been asking for-true SVGA resolution at 800 x 600 pixels. This, combined with the superior brightness of 500 ANSI lumens, gives the DP5600 razor-sharp, brilliant images, even in well-lit rooms. Weighing just 16.5 pounds, this road-worthy projector is one convenient multimedia peripheral.
<p>
Exceptionally easy to set up and use, the DP5600 has a motorized 1.6:1 zoom 
lens that allows you to position the projector almost anywhere in the room. 
Four-position image control provides even greater flexibility by allowing for 
front-, rear-, or ceiling-mounted projection. And, if your computer is 
connected serially to the projector, you can control both from anywhere in 
the room with the full-featured remote control. Like all <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> <A HREF="../Solutions/solutions.html">multimedia projectors</A>, the DP5600 is compatible with virtually all PCs and Macintosh computers, and worldwide video capability is also a standard feature. 
<p>
<center>
<table border = 4>
	<tr>
		<td align = center><font size = "+1">&#160Download a <A HREF="dp5600.pdf"><IMG SRC="gifs/pdf_logo.gif" width = 28 height = 31 border = none></A> file of the new <A HREF="dp5600.pdf">DP 5600 datasheet</A>! </td>
	</tr>
</table>
</center>
<p>
<B>The lightweight Desktop Projector 5600 is a presenters dream.</B>
<p>
<UL>
<LI>Displays vivid SVGA (800 x 600) images true to your computer's output.
<LI>Projects extremely bright, fully saturated colors for eye-catching 
multimedia presentations, even in a well-lit room.
<LI>Advanced features packed in a portable 16.5-pound projector.
<LI>Connect your PC or Macintosh for computer-based presentations.
<LI>Position the Desktop Projector 5600 anywhere in the room.
<LI>Adjust the motorized zoom lens for image size and to sharpen the focus.
<LI>Connect a laserdisc player or VCR to project video with stereo audio.</font>
</UL>
<p>
<br>

<center>
[&#160 <A HREF="../University/university.html">Presenters University</A>&#160 |&#160 <A HREF="../Solving/solving.html">Support And Service</A>&#160 |&#160 
<A HREF="../Partnering/partnering.html">Resellers Forum</A>&#160 ]
<br>
