<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The New Lightbook Projector!</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_products.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/new_products_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "New Products"></A>
<p>
<H2>With the <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Lightbook Projector, making a big<br>impression on the road has never been easier.</H2>
</center>

<IMG SRC="gifs/lightbook.gif" align = right width = 288 height = 199 alt = "Photo of Lightbook" hspace = 6>
<font size = "+2"><B>T</B></font><font size = "+1">he <font color = "FF0000">Proxima<sup><font size = "-1">&reg;</font></font></sup> Lightbook<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup> projector is designed specifically for you--the traveling executive. Weighing just 11 pounds, and small enough to fit into a small attache case, the <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=LB10&sction=Description">Lightbook projector</A> is the most reliable and trustworthy traveling companion you'll ever have. It's a small projector that packs a big punch in the conference room!
<p>
And even in the smallest rooms, <A HREF="lightbook.html">the Lightbook projector makes your big ideas look bigger and brighter</A>. Its sharp, high-contrast image looks great--even with the lights on. When your ideas are big, bright, and colorful, people pay attention. 
<p>
<UL>
<LI>Lightweight, compact design makes traveling and presenting virtually effortless
<LI>Projects big, bright, high-contrast images-even when the projector is close to the screen
<LI>Secure, ergonomic design and intuitive user interface make it the ideal tool for executive presenters
</UL>
<p>
<center>
<table border = 4>
	<tr>
		<td align = center><font size = "+1">&#160Download a <A HREF="lightbook.pdf"><IMG SRC="gifs/pdf_logo.gif" width = 28 height = 31 border = none></A> file of the new <A HREF="lightbook.pdf">Lightbook datasheet</A>! </td>
	</tr>
</table>
</center>
<p>
<B>Pay attention to your audience, not your projector.</B>
<p>
The Lightbook projector is easy to set up and use, giving you the freedom to think about your message, not your projector. Place it on the end of a conference table, connect it to your computer, and you're ready to present! And the Lightbook projector's intuitive user interface makes presenting as simple as clicking your mouse.
<p>
To display the optimum image size, most projectors force you to move them back and forth on the conference table--taking your valuable time and distracting your audience. In today's fast-paced business world, you can't afford to spend your precious time setting up your equipment. The Lightbook projector works best right where you expect it--out of the way, at the front of the conference table. And it's so easy to connect, that you'll have extra time to work with your audience. 
<p>
<B>Form follows function.</B>
<p>
Life on the road can be rough. That's why the LightBook projector was designed to handle the rigors of travel. When you close the Lightbook projector, the sensitive optics are securely stowed inside a sleek protective case. Add to that a sturdy metal frame, and you've got one tough traveling companion.
<p>
<IMG SRC="gifs/lightbook2.gif" align = left width = 243 height = 180 alt = "Photo of Lightbook When Opened" hspace = 9>Once you've reached your destination, opening the projector is easy. Simply press the lock-release buttons, lift the cover, and open the protective lens cover. When you're finished with your presentation, it's just as easy to safely and securely close your Lightbook projector. Simply reverse the opening procedures and you're ready to hit the road.
<p>
As an added bonus, your Lightbook projector comes with a sleek executive-styled carrying case that is small, compact, and portable. With your new projector safe and secure, you can focus on your next destination.
<br clear = all>
<br>
<B>Features</B>
<p>
<UL>
<LI>Lightweight (11 pounds) and small enough (13.5 x 9.25 x 5 inches) to fit under an airplane seat with plenty of room to spare
<LI>Produces a big, bright picture from the front of the room--so it never gets in your way
<LI>Unique optical design ensures that your image won't be blocked or obstructed by the meeting room table top
<LI>Keystone correction adjustments always ensure a uniform image
<LI>Compatible with the Kensington Security Standard to secure the projector when you leave it unattended
<LI>Compatible with a wide range of PC and Macintosh computers
<LI>VGA (640 x 480) resolution with plug-and-play SVGA support
<LI>Fit-to-View<sup><font size = "-1">&#174;</font></sup> feature for full-screen 800 x 600 images and panning of full-resolution images
<LI>Backup bulb for on-the-fly lamp changes
<LI>International power supply for use anywhere in the world
<LI>LightBoard<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup> drawing tool for highlighting and drawing on the projected image
<LI>Cyclops<sup><font size = "-1">&#174;</font></sup> remote control for mouse-like operations
<LI>Cyclops Quick Remote for executive control
<LI>Backlit control panel that is always easy to see
</UL>
<p>
<B>The Lightbook was designed specifically to setup and go.</B>
<p>
Connect your laptop for computer-based presentations on the road.
<p>
Connect a VCR or laserdisc for multimedia presentations.
<p>
The Lightbook can be placed anywhere on a table and it will never cut off the image.
<p>
Display large images even when the projector is placed at the front of the room.
<p>
Use the Cyclops remote with Cyclops F/X software for easy control of your presentation.
<p>
<br>

<center>
