<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Proxima Technical Support</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor = "#ffffff">
<center>
<A HREF="solving.map"><IMG SRC="jpgs/header.jpg" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Support And Services"></A>
</center>
<p><center><b><font COLOR="#0000A0"><font SIZE=+3>Tech Talk</font><br></FONT></b>
<br></center>
Welcome to Tech Talk!  This section will feature a tip or suggestion for using 
Proxima products.  It will be updated frequently so be sure and visit again!<p>
<hr>
<!------- BEGIN------->
<I><SCRIPT LANGUAGE="JavaScript">
<!-- hide
document.write("Last modified: "+document.lastModified);
 // end hiding -->
</SCRIPT>
</I><p>
<B>I am unable to obtain an image when the DP5600 is connected to a computer or the computer image fades. What do I do?</B><p>

Sometimes the DP5600 is unable to determine the type of signal coming from the computer. With the remote control:<p>
<ol>
<li>Press MENU.
<li>Choose Setting, then PC ADJUSTMENT.
<li>Choose any mode to use under the "WHERE TO RESERVE" menu.
<li>Choose MEMORY, then QUIT.<p>
</ol><br>
<I>NOTE: The image may go back to the previous settings. If so, the new mode must be selected. Press MENU, then SYSTEM, then choose SEARCH.</I><br>
<p>

<center>
[&#160 <A HREF="../University/university.html">Presenters University</A>&#160 |&#160<!A HREF="solving.html">Support And Service<!/A>&#160 |&#160<A HREF="../Partnering/partnering.html">Resellers Forum</A>&#160 ]<br>[&#160 
