	</tr>
</table>
<p>
<font size = "+1">To take advantage of the full power of your <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> LCD projection product, look no further than <font color = "BF0000"><B>Microsoft<sup><font size = -1>&#174;</font></sup> PowerPoint<sup><font size = -1>&#174;</font></sup> for Windows<sup><font size = -1>&#174;</font></sup> 95</B></font>. With PowerPoint, your <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> system becomes a powerful tool, delivering professional-looking slides that help you get the results you want quickly and easily.
<IMG SRC="gifs/microsoft1.gif" width = 126 height = 160 align = right hspace = 9 alt = "Microsoft PowerPoint for Windows 95">
<p>
PowerPoint for Windows 95 has been designed to fit all your presentation needs--from small interactive meetings to large-scale formal presentations. With hundreds of templates that provide content advice, you always know what points to cover. Advanced tools for creating animated multimedia presentations with sound and video are new to PowerPoint, as are features that handle creating sophisticated handout pages, meeting minutes documents, compressed presentations on floppy disks, and more.
<p>
These powerful advances are provided in an easy-to-use format that looks and acts just like the other members of the Microsoft Office family of programs, so that everyone in your group can quickly get up to speed.
<p>
<table cellspacing = 0 cellpadding = 3 border = 1>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>Features:</B></td>
		<td valign = top><LI> AutoClipArt scans slides and suggests clip art for your presentation.<BR>
<LI> Multiple Undo makes it easy to remove all your recent edits.<BR>
<LI> Answer Wizard provides help when you type in a question.<BR>
<LI> Meeting Minder offers a way to capture minutes and action items during your presentation.<BR>
<LI> ValuPack is a collection of sound, video, clip art, and textures that adds sizzle to your slides.<BR>
<LI> Animation Settings let you animate any item on-screen during a slide show.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>Price:</B></td>
		<td valign = top>Estimated retail prices--$129.00 for existing owners of PowerPoint or competing products, $339.00 for new users.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>Requirements:</B></td>
		<td valign = top>386DX or higher processor; Microsoft Windows 95 or Windows NT Workstation version 3.51 or later; 6 MB RAM on Windows 95 (12 MB on NT); 14 MB disk space; 3.52 high density disk drive or CD-ROM drive; VGA or higher video adapter.</td>
	</tr>
</table>
