<HEAD>
<TITLE> Presentation Resource Center - SMART Technologies Inc. </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink = "AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center> 
<A HREF="univ_resource.map"><IMG SRC="../gifs/resource_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Presentation Resource Center"></A>
</center>

<p>
<IMG SRC="gifs/smart_logo.gif" width = 216 height = 72 alt = "SMART Technologies Inc. Logo" align = left hspace = 12>
<table cellspacing = 0 cellpadding = 3>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><font size = "+1"><B>Company:</B></td>
		<td valign = top><font size = "+1"><font color = "BF0000"><B>SMART Technologies Inc.</B></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>Address:</B></td>
		<td valign = top>Suite 600, 1177 11th Avenue S.W.<br>Calgary, AB, Canada, T2R 1K9</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>Phone Sales:</B></td>
		<td valign = top>(403) 245-0333</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>Fax:</B></td>
		<td valign = top>(403) 245-0366</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>E-Mail:</B></td>
		<td valign = top><A HREF="mailto:sales@smarttech.com">sales@smarttech.com</A></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>WWW:</B></td>
		<td valign = top><A HREF="http://www.smarttech.com">http://www.smarttech.com</A></td>
	</tr>
</table>
<p>
<font size = "+1">The <font color = "BF0000"><B>SMART Board</B></font> is an interactive electronic whiteboard  that dramatically improves the effectiveness of your meetings and training sessions by allowing you to naturally bring computer power into your meeting room. All this is provided in a solution that works, looks, and feels like a regular whiteboard.
<IMG SRC="gifs/smart1.gif" HEIGHT=140 WIDTH=173 alt = "Photo of SMART Technologies Inc. Product" align = right hspace = 6>
<p>
Once you display your computer information onto the 4' by 3' SMART Board using any LCD panel or LCD projector, simply touch on the Board to control software and bring up documents, spreadsheets, or designs. With the SMART Board it is natural and easy to use your software during a meeting. Plus, you can still use the SMART Board as a whiteboard--simply pick up a marker, and write notes with colorful electronic ink over any projected image. All this can be done on a large interactive whiteboard that everyone in the room can see.
<p>
You can also use the SMART Board without a projector to capture whiteboard notes immediately on your computer. The SMART Board recognizes four colors of pens and an eraser, so you can write as you would on an ordinary whiteboard. After meetings, you can print, e-mail, or copy and paste your notes into other applications.</font>
<br clear = right>
<br>
<table cellspacing = 0 cellpadding = 3 border = 1>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>Features:</B></td>
		<td valign = top><UL><LI> Touch on the Board to control Windows or Macintosh software.<br>
<LI> Annotate any projected image with electronic ink.<br>
<LI> Print and save all whiteboard notes.<br>
<LI> Utilize built-in multipoint conferencing software.<br>
<LI> Receive four dry markers and eraser.<br>
<LI> Connect the board to a computer serial port.<br>
<LI> Use with any LCD projector.<br>
<LI> Optional roll-about floor stand.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>Price:</B></td>
		<td valign = top>SMART Board (wall-mounted): $2,999.00<br>
Floor stand: $649.00</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>Requirements:</B></td>
		<td valign = top>Available serial port<br>
Windows: 386 or higher processor; 4 MB RAM; MS-DOS 5.0 or higher; Windows 3.1 or higher (including Windows 95). Macintosh:&#174; 68020 or later processor; System 7 or higher.</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<p>

