		<td>$360.00</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>Inertia, a workstation (high resolution) to VGA standards converter</td>
		<td>$5,995.00</td>
	</tr>
</table>
</menu>
<p>
<B>Cables & Adapters</B>
<menu>
<table border=1>
	<tr>
		<td>MBC-LCD VGA Cable, a Y-type cable for use with VGA comptuer, monitor and Proxima</td>
		<td>$125.00</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>MBC-LCD Mac II Cable, a Y-type cable for use with Macintosh comptuer, monitor and Proxima</td>
		<td>$125.00</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>15 HD-LC25, a VGA laptop to Proxima 25 pin input</td>
		<td>$85.00</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>15 D(35)-LC25, a Mac 640x480 laptop to Proxima 25 pin input
		<td>$85.00</td>
	</tr>
</table>
</menu>
<p>
<IMG SRC="gifs/extron1.gif" width = 158 height = 153 alt = "Photo of Extron Electronics Switchers" align = right hspace = 9>
<br>
<font size = "+1">The <font color = "BF0000"><B>SW VGA Switchers</B></font> are two, four or six input, one output 15 pin HD (15 pin D for Macintosh version) bi-directional switchers. The SW 2 VGA is compatible with IBM PS/2, VGA, Super VGA, VESA, XGA, and XGA-2 computers. The optional Macintosh/VGA adapter allows for cross platform, Macintosh and VGA, switching (see diagram). These SW VGA Switchers are all housed in 2U high metal enclosures, which are rack mountable for easy installation. They are compatible with all VGA and Macintosh compatible Proxima LCD Panels and Projectors. All Switchers are also available in an auto-switch version.</font>
<br clear = all>
<br>
<table cellspacing = 0 cellpadding = 3 border = 1>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>Features:</B></td>
		<td valign = top><LI> 250 MHz Bandwidth<br>
<LI> ID bits switched for bi-directional input/output switching<br>
<LI> Female 15 pin HD VGA style input/output connectors<br>
<LI> Tactile switch buttons with internal LEDs<br>
<LI> Male to male VGA cable for input to SW 2 VGA<br>
<LI> Remote connector (contact closure)<br>
<LI> Macintosh compatible with optional adapter</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><B>Price:</B></td>
		<td valign = top>SW 2 VGA: $360.00 (115 volt: 60-099-01, 230 volt: 60-099-02)<br>
SW 4 VGA: $550.00 (115 volt: 60-136-01, 230 volt: 60-136-02)<br>
SW 6 VGA: $795.00 (115 volt: 60-137-01, 230 volt: 60-137-02)</td>
	</tr>
