<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE> Field Note: #40 </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor = "#ffffff">
<center>

<A HREF="solving.map"><IMG SRC="jpgs/header.jpg" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Support And Services"></A>

<H2>Field Note:  #40</H2>

</center>



<br>

<B>Date:</B> December 15, 1995

<P>

<B>Subject:</B>   Compatibility with Laptop Computers that use 800x600

TFT Display

<P>

<br>

<H3>PROBLEM</H3>

When you try to display an image from a notebook computer that

has an 800x600 internal LCD screen, the projected image is either

missing information from the top/bottom, compressed from left/right,

or does not appear at all.

<P>

<br>

<H3>DISCUSSION</H3>

Notebook computer manufacturers such as NEC, Toshiba, Compaq,

and AST are producing computers that use an 800x600 TFT internal

display.  When the video display mode is set to simultaneous internal/external

display, the video output is always 800x600 resolution, regardless

of the display setting made in Windows (or Windows 95, OS/2, etc.).

This signal will not work with Proxima display products that require

640x480 signals.

<P>

The computer will have to be configured to provide a true 640x480

external video signal, which means that the computer will not

be able to display an image on its internal screen and the Proxima

LCD panel at the same time.

<P>

<br>

<H3>SOLUTION</H3>

To configure the external video signal to 640x480 mode:

<OL>

	<LI> Set the PC display resolution to 640x480.  This is done through

Windows Setup    (Win 3.1) or Control Panel, Display Icon (Windows

95).<p>

	<LI> Connect the Proxima product to the computer using the appropriate

cable.<p>

	<LI> Configure the PC to display video only on the external video

port.  This is usually done through a combination of keystrokes

(such as FN+F3) or a hardware setup program (consult you computer

documentation for details).<p>

	<LI> Re-start Windows to set the external video to 640x480 mode.

 The image will appear on the LCD panel.  Sync and frequency adjustments

may be needed.<p>

</OL>



<center>
[&#160 <A HREF="../University/university.html">Presenters University</A>&#160 |&#160<!A HREF="solving.html">Support And Service<!/A>&#160 |&#160<A HREF="../Partnering/partnering.html">Resellers Forum</A>&#160 ]<br>[&#160 
<A HREF="../New/new.html">What's Hot</A>&#160 |&#160 <A HREF="../Solutions/index.html">Proxima Products</A>&#160 |&#160<A HREF="../About/about.html">About Proxima</A>&#160 ]<p>[&#160 <A HREF="../home.html">Home Page</A>&#160 ]
<br>
</center>

