<h2>Notebook/Laptop Computer Video Port Activation Chart</h2>
<FONT SIZE=-1>Updated 12/20/96</FONT>
<hr>
<p>Most notebook/laptop computers can't display their internal screens and activate the external video port at the same time. This chart provides some of the 
commands for switching back and forth between the screen and the video port for common notebook/laptop computers. Some computers have more than 
one command depending on the model. If all models use the same command, only one command is shown. </p>
<p></p>
<div align=left>
<TABLE BORDER=1>
<TR>
<TD><B>Computer
Manufacturer</B></TD>
<TD><B>Model</B></TD>
<TD><B>Activate Video Port</B></TD>
<TD><B>De-Activate Video Port</B></TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>Acer</TD>
<TD>Note 950</TD>
<TD>CTRL-ALT-F3 button above function keys activates a setup menu. Set display mode to Both</TD>
<TD>CTRL-ALT-F3</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD> </TD>
<TD>760IC</TD>
<TD>CTRL-ALT-ESC from Dos prompt</TD>
<TD>CTRL-ALT-ESC from Dos prompt</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD> </TD>
<TD>Note Lite 350PC</TD>
<TD>Must be terminated w/ A936 connector</TD>
<TD> </TD>
</TR>
