<HTML>
<HEAD> 
<TITLE> Field Note: #37a </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor = "#ffffff">
<center>
<A HREF="solving.map"><IMG SRC="jpgs/header.jpg" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Support And Services"></A>
<H2>Field Note:  #37a</H2>
</center>

<P>
May 23, 1996
<P>
Subject:  Silicon Graphics Indy/Indigo<SUP><FONT SIZE=2>2</FONT></SUP>
connection to Proxima Ovation+920
<P>
Field Note: #37A<I> (Replaces Field Note #37 dated December 2,
1994)<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
</I>
<P>
 <U><B>PROBLEM<BR>
</B></U>
<P>
Connecting Silicon Graphics Workstations, including models Indy
or Indigo<SUP><FONT SIZE=2>2</FONT></SUP>, to the Proxima Ovation+920
using the Proxima C801-6 video cable results in an image that
cannot be stabilized.  In addition, the range of the vertical
adjustment is not wide enough to move the image sufficiently to
allow viewing the complete image.<BR>

<P>
<U><B>DISCUSSION<BR>
</B></U>
<P>
SGI video cards support Sync on green, Composite Sync and Separate
Sync, depending on the monitor connected.  Indy and Indigo<SUP><FONT SIZE=2>2</FONT></SUP>
systems use a Sony monitor that only uses Sync on green.  The
Proxima Ovation+920 panel can support either Sync on green, or
Composite Sync, depending on the input from the computer.  The
Proxima C801-6 video cable passes all of the sync signals to the
Proxima Ovation+920.  However, connecting the SGI video to the
Proxima Ovation+920 panel using the Proxima C801-6 cable applies
all three sync signals to the Proxima Ovation+920 simultaneously,
but not on the correct pins.  This causes confusion in the Proxima
Ovation+920, resulting in an unusable image.<BR>

<P>
<U><B>SOLUTION<BR>
</B></U>
<P>
When connecting a Proxima Ovation+920 to Silicon Graphics Workstations,
including all Indy and Indigo<SUP><FONT SIZE=2>2</FONT></SUP>
models, use the Proxima SGI Cable Kit, A36.  The SGI Cable Kit
contains two C943-6 SGI 13C3 to 13C3 connector cables.  This kit:
<BR>

<UL>
<LI>Allows connection of a Proxima Ovation+920 to an SGI workstation
without a monitor; sense lines are supported.
<LI>Supports all SGI monitor sync configurations.
<LI>Supports all SGI video systems.
</UL>

<P>

<P>
To order, contact your local Proxima dealer or Customer Service
at 1-800-447-7694, option #1.<BR>
<BR>
<center>[&#160 <A HREF="../University/university.html">Presenters University</A>&#160 |&#160<!A HREF="solving.html">Support And Service<!/A>&#160 |&#160<A HREF="../Partnering/partnering.html">Resellers Forum</A>&#160 ]<br>[&#160 
<A HREF="../New/new.html">What's Hot</A>&#160 |&#160 <A HREF="../Solutions/index.html">Proxima Products</A>&#160 |&#160<A HREF="../About/about.html">About Proxima</A>&#160 ]<p>[&#160 <A HREF="../home.html">Home Page</A>&#160 ]
<br>
</center>
