<HEAD> 
<TITLE> Field Note: #39 </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor = "#ffffff">
<center>

<A HREF="solving.map"><IMG SRC="jpgs/header.jpg" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Support And Services"></A>
<H2>Field Note:  #39</H2>

</center>



<br>

<B>Date:</B> December 15, 1995

<P>

<B>Subject:</B>   Desktop Projector Operating Temperature in High Altitude

<P>

<br>

<H3>PROBLEM</H3>

<P>

When used at a high altitude Desktop Projector models 2xxx can

overheat at a lower room temperature than when used at Sea Level.

<P>

<br>

<H3>DISCUSSION</H3>

<P>

The maximum ambient (room) temperature for operating Desktop Projector

models 2xxx is  80o F     (27o C).  Operating the Desktop Projector

in an environment with a higher ambient temperature will cause

the LCD panel to overheat.

<P>

The maximum ambient operating temperature for the Desktop Projector

decreases 1o C for every 1000' (305m) increase in altitude.  The

maximum operating altitude for Desktop Projector models 2xxx is

5000' (1524m) above Sea Level.

<P>

<br>

<H3>SOLUTION</H3>

<P>

The following table shows the maximum ambient operating temperature

for Desktop Projector models  2xxx at various altitudes.  Using

the Desktop Projector above 5000' may not provide sufficient cooling

for the projector.<p>



<HR>



<p>

<TABLE border>

	<TR>

		<TD>&#160 <B>Altitude</B></TD>

		<TD>&#160 <B>Maximum Temperature</B> </TD>

	</TR>    

	<TR>

		<TD>&#160 Sea Level</TD>

		<TD>&#160 80 F  27o C</TD>

	</TR>

	<TR>

		<TD>&#160 1000' (305 m) </TD>

		<TD>&#160 78.8 F  26 C</TD>

	</TR>

	<TR>

		<TD>&#160 2000' (610 m) </TD>

		<TD>&#160 77 F  25 C</TD>

	</TR>

	<TR>

		<TD>&#160 3000' (915 m) </TD>

		<TD>&#160 75 F  24 C</TD>

	</TR>

	<TR>

		<TD>&#160 4000' (1220 m) </TD>

		<TD>&#160 73.4 F  23 C</TD>

	</TR>

	<TR>

		<TD>&#160 5000' (1525 m) </TD>

		<TD>&#160 71.6 F  22 C</TD>

	</TR>

</TABLE>

<P>



<center>
[&#160 <A HREF="../University/university.html">Presenters University</A>&#160 |&#160<!A HREF="solving.html">Support And Service<!/A>&#160 |&#160<A HREF="../Partnering/partnering.html">Resellers Forum</A>&#160 ]<br>[&#160 
