<HEAD>
<TITLE>Frequently Asked Questions - General Information</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor = "#ffffff">

<center>
<A HREF="solving.map"><IMG SRC="jpgs/header.jpg" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Support And Services"></A>
</center>

<br>
<H2>General Information</H2>
<OL TYPE=1, 2, 3, ...>
<LI><B>What power supply will work with my Proxima unit?</B>
<P>
To order any of the following power supplies, please contact your local Authorized Proxima Reseller or Proxima Customer Service at: 800-447-7694, option 2.
<p>
<TABLE BORDER=1>
<TR>
	<TD><B>Product</B></TD>
	<TD><B>Part #</B></TD>
	<TD><B>Voltage/Connector</B></TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD>Data Display A400</TD>
	<TD>400-00008</TD>
	<TD>110 V North American<br> 9VDC 800mA positive tip</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD>VersaColor II</TD>
	<TD>400-00015<br>400-00016<br>400-00017</TD>
	<TD>110V North American<br>220V Europe<br>220V British</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD>Multimode II</TD>
	<TD>400-00012<br>400-00013<br>400-00014<br>400-00021</TD>
	<TD>110V North American<br>220V Europe<br>220V UK<br>220V Worldwide</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD>ColorWorks<br>Ovation Value Line</TD>
	<TD>400-00018</TD>
	<TD>110/220 Auto switching</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD>Ovation+ 84x<br>Ovation+ 920<br>Ovation+ 944</TD>
	<TD>400-00018-5</TD>
	<TD>110/220 Auto switching</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<p>
<LI><B>What type of screen is best to use?</B>  
<P>
It is best to use a white matte screen. High gain screens have a narrow view angle and may cause problems with Cyclops.  
<P>
<LI><B>What is the aspect ratio of a 640x480 screen?</B>  
<P>
The aspect ratio of a 640x480 image is 4:3 (Horizontal to Vertical.)
<p>
<LI> <B>How do I convert diagonal image size to a height and width dimension?</B>  
<P>
Think of the diagonal image size as the hypotenuse of a right triangle, where the hypotenuse = 5, the height = 3, an the width = 4.  The other dimensions are then easy to figure out.  For example, if the diagonal measurement is 75 inches, take the 75 and divide by 5, which equals 15.  The height would then be 3 x 15 or 45 inches and the width would be 4 x 15 or 60 inches.  Your screen size is therefore 45" H by 60" W.  To get the number in feet, you then divide by 12.
<P>
<LI><B>What is the warranty period on Proxima projection products?</B>
<P>
The standard warranty period is 1 year from date of purchase.  Please note that extended warranties can be purchased from our dealers.
<P>
<LI><B>What information do I need to return a Proxima product for repair?</B>
<P>
To have a Proxima product repaired, it must have a RMA (Return Material Authorization) number.  Call Technical Support with the following information to get a RMA number:  product model number, serial number, date code, and description of the problem.  Technical Support may request a fax of the invoice or packing slip to verify warranty status of the product. 
</OL>
<P>

