<P>
<LI><B>What are the input specifications for the DP4100z/4200z?</B>
<p>
Input specifications (minimum to maximum) are as follows:<p>
DP4100z (VGA) Computer Graphics

<ul><p>Hsync min - max : 15 KHz to 40 KHz<br>
Vsync min - max : 49.5 Hz to 75.1 Hz<br>
Pix clk min- max : 12 to 31.7 MHz</ul>
<p>
DP4200z (SVGA) Computer Graphics:
<ul><p>Hsync min - max : 15K Hz to 50 KHz<br>
Vsync min - max : 49.5 Hz to 75 Hz<br>
Pix clk min- max : 12 to 51 MHz</ul>
<p>
DP4100z and DP4200z Video (same for both)
<ul><p>
Hsync min - max : 15 KHz to 16 KHz<br>
Vsync min - max : 49 to 51 Hz and 59 to 61 Hz<br>
Pix clk min- max : 12 to 15 MHz</ul>
<p>
<LI><B>When displaying a PAL input video source on my DP4200Z, the image is pixelated, or digitized.  What's wrong?</B><p>
Please contact your local Proxima dealer for information on obtaining a firmware upgrade to resolve this issue.  To locate a dealer near you, call Proxima at: 619-457-5500.
<P>
