<HR>
<P>
<EM><H3><A NAME="dp5xxx">Desktop Projector 5100/5500</A></H3></EM>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<OL TYPE=1, 2, 3, ...>
<LI><B>What inputs/outputs are on the DP5100/DP5500?</B>   
<P>
The DP5100 has two computer, two video and 4 audio inputs ports.  There are no output ports.
<BR>
The DP5500 has the following inputs: two computer, two video and 4 audio ports.  For output, the DP5500 has: monitor (PC/MAC), stereo audio , RS-232 and Cyclops ports.  


<P>
<LI><B>Does the DP5100/DP5500 have a zoom lens?</B>  
<P>
Yes, the DP5100 has a motorized 1.6 to 1 zoom lens and focus control, adjustable from the remote control or projector's keypad.   
<P>
<LI><B>How can I use a monitor with the DP5100?</B>    
<P>
Use a distribution amplifier which connects to computer input and distributes the video signal to a local monitor and the DP5100.  Model numbers for Proxima distribution amplifiers are as follows:
<P>
<TABLE BORDER=1>
        <TR>
                <TD WIDTH=132>A51-1 </TD>
                <TD WIDTH=167>VGA, 110V</TD>
        </TR>

        <TR>
                <TD WIDTH=132>A51-2 </TD>
                <TD WIDTH=167>VGA, 220V</TD>
        </TR>

        <TR>
                <TD WIDTH=132>A51-3 </TD>
                <TD WIDTH=167>MAC, 110V </TD>
        </TR>

        <TR>
                <TD WIDTH=132>A51-4 </TD>
                <TD WIDTH=167>MAC, 220V </TD>
        </TR>

</TABLE>

<P>
<LI><B>Is there a ceiling mount bracket available for the DP5100/DP5500?</B>   
<P>
Yes, there is a ceiling mount bracket available through Progressive Marketing Products (part number: PBM510).  You can reach Progressive Marketing Products at (800) 368-9700 or (714) 255-0775.
<P>
<LI><STRONG>What is the typical lamp life for the DP5100 and the DP5500 lamps?</STRONG>  
<P>
The DP5100 has a typical lamp life of 1,000 hours and the DP5500 is rated at 2000 hours.  The rating is how long the lamp will project up to 50% of its initial brightness.
<P>
<LI><B>What is the part number of a replacement lamp for the DP5100 and DP5500?</B> 
<P>
The metal halide lamp for the DP5100 and DP5500 can easily be replaced by the customer.  The replacement lamp part number for the DP5100 is 160-00072.  The DP5500 replacement lamp is L84.
<P>
<LI><B>Since the DP5100  does not provide an audio output jack, how can I handle audio output?</B><P>
The DP5100 has a superb internal audio amplifier and high-fidelity speaker that is useful when making presentations for small to medium sized groups.  For larger groups and/or audio-intensive multimedia presentations, external sound systems powered directly from the computer or video source are generally employed.
<P>
<LI><B> What type of carrying cases are available for the DP5100 or the DP5500?</B>
<P>    
<TABLE BORDER=1>
        <TR>
                <TD WIDTH=72> A300 </TD>
                <TD WIDTH=366>Hard Case, includes a pull handle and wheels for easy portability. This case can be checked at the airline counter. Rugged construction ensures optimum protection.</TD>
        </TR>

        <TR>
                <TD WIDTH=72> A298 </TD>
                <TD WIDTH=366>Rolling Soft Case, includes a pull handle and wheels for easy portability. It is designed to accommodate the DP5100, but can easily be customized to fit any Desktop Projector simply by repositioning the padding.</TD>
        </TR>
</TABLE>
