<HEAD>
<TITLE>Frequently Asked Questions -Cyclops</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor = "#ffffff">

<center>
<A HREF="solving.map"><IMG SRC="jpgs/header.jpg" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Support And Services"></A>
</center>

<br>
<H2>Cyclops</H2>

<OL TYPE=1, 2, 3, ...>
<LI><B>What are the current drivers for Cyclops?</B>
<P> 
<TABLE BORDER=1>
	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=66><B>Version</B></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=120><B>Operating System</B></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=397><B>Description</B></TD>
	</TR>

	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=66><A HREF="maccy21frm.html" NAME="Macintosh Cyclops driver">2.1</A></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=120>Macintosh</TD>
		<TD WIDTH=397>System 6.X+, loads in System Folder, emulates a one-button mouse.</TD>
	</TR>

	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=66><A HREF="cyc301frm.html" NAME="Cyclops Driver 3.01">3.01</A></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=120>OS/2 2.0, 2.1+</TD>
		<TD WIDTH=397>Works best with Microsoft Mouse.</TD>
	</TR>
	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=66><A HREF="win95frm.html" NAME="Cyclops 4.2 Driver" TITLE="Cyclops 4.2 Driver">4.2</A></TD>
</TD>
		<TD WIDTH=177>Windows 95 and Windows 3.x</TD>
		<TD WIDTH=378>Installed as a device driver. </TD>
	</TR>


</TABLE>
<p>
<LI><B>After installing the Cyclops 4.2 driver for Windows 95 on my laptop,  the "Proxima Devices" icon in Control Panel indicates that "No Proxima devices were detected."  Thus, the mouse arrow will not follow the Cyclops wand (or laser).  How is this corrected?</B>
<p>
The Proxima display device must have a stable input video signal that can be viewed on the screen before Windows 95 boots.  If not, the Cyclops 4.2 driver will not detect the Cyclops camera in the Proxima unit.  
<p>
Follow these steps to correct the problem:<p>
<ol>
<li>Connect the Proxima display device to your laptop before powering up either unit.  Now, power up the Proxima display device then the laptop.<br>
<li> Toggle the video signal over to the display device using your laptops appropriate key sequence.  (e.g. Compaq uses Fn + F4, check your laptops Users Guide on how to do this or check our <A HREF="faq_notebook.html">Notebook Video Port Activation Chart</A> on the Internet). <br>
<li> To determine whether the Cyclops driver successfully detected the Cyclops camera, launch the "Proxima Devices" Icon in Control Panel.<br>
<p>
If you see something similar to the following, it was successful:<br>
<B>Proxima Cyclops Driver<br>
Driver version 4.2<br>
Virtual Driver Version: Unknown (requires 1.30 or higher)<br>
Panel ID: 78 (Each display device ID is unique)<br>
Panel Firmware Version: 1.0<br>
Cyclops ID: 3<br>
Cyclops Firmware Version: 1.3<br>
Select OK to update .INI file.</B><br>
<p>
You will see the following if it was unsuccessful:<br>
<B>Proxima Cyclops Driver<br>
Driver version 4.2<br>
Virtual Driver Version: Unknown (requires 1.30 or higher)<br>
No Proxima devices were detected.<br>
Select OK to update .INI file.</B>
<p>
<li>If the Cyclops camera was found, continue on with the Cyclops calibration procedure.
<li>If the Cyclops camera was NOT found, consult the <A HREF="pdfs/Cyclops.pdf">Cyclops Users Guide</A> for troubleshooting information or contact us at 800-447-7694, option 2.
</ol>

<P>
<LI><B>Why is the mouse jumping around the screen?</B>  
<P>
If the computer has an AUX port or QuickPort style mouse and the mouse is jumping around the screen, version 3.01 of the Cyclops driver may not be compatible.  Please contact Technical Support for more information on resolving this issue.
<P>
<LI><B>With a ballpoint mouse and Windows 3.x, how do I set the mouse back to original driver after installing version 3.01 of the Cyclops driver?</B>   
<P>
After you change the mouse driver, the computer tries to go back to original mouse and Windows cannot find it.  Copy MOUSE.DRV (original mouse driver i.e.; from ballpt or bpmouse directory) into WINDOWS\SYSTEM directory.  Choose MS or PS/2 Mouse in Windows SETUP.
<P>
<LI><B>What should I do when the "Cyclops Not Detected" message appears as Windows 3.x is loaded?</B> <P> 
This message means there is no communication between the computer and Cyclops. 
<P>
<TABLE BORDER>
	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=48 valign = top>1. </TD>
		<TD WIDTH=535>Check the Cyclops camera unit itself. Does Cyclops beep when the projector/panel is turned on? Does it respond to calibration initiation?</TD>
	</TR>

	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=48 valign = top>2. </TD>
		<TD WIDTH=535>Check the connections/power. Is the Cyclops cable plugged into computer (serial port) and projector/panel (RS 232/Cyclops port)? Is it securely connected?</TD>
	</TR>

	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=48 valign = top>3. </TD>
		<TD WIDTH=535>Check the serial cable. Are any of the pins on the cable pushed in or bent?</TD>
	</TR>

	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=48 valign = top>4. </TD>
		<TD WIDTH=535>Check the serial port on the computer. Cyclops must be on COM1 or COM2. Is there an internal modem in the PC? If so, the modem needs to be disabled or set to a com port/IRQ that does not interfere. Is there a PCMCIA card in the PC? If so, it needs to be disabled. To check serial communication, run CYDOS program (on Cyclops installation diskettes, in PROXIMA directory.)</TD>
	</TR>
</TABLE>

<P>
Note: With 2020, 2030, and 2060, if you get &quot;Cyclops not detected&quot; message and everything appears fine (serial connections, etc.), disconnect the serial cable and cycle 
power on panel/projector, then reconnect the cable and continue.
<P>
<LI><B>I get the message "This version of pointer options require MOUSE.DRV or later."</B>   
<P>
This is only a notification and does not keep Cyclops from working properly.  This message can be eliminated by editing WIN.INI and removing any reference to pointer.exe from the LOAD= statement.  This will not affect your mouse in any way.
<P>
<LI><B>Which should I turn on first, the projector/panel or the computer?</B>  
<P>
Turn on the projector/panel first, then the computer.  
<P>
<LI><B>Cyclops has been calibrated and the mouse pointer follows the Cyclops pointer, so why can't I click on anything?</B>  
<P>
Check in Windows, Control Panel, Mouse, to see if "Swap Left/Right Buttons" is checked.
  This option should not be checked.  With the Ovation+84X, Ovation+9xx panels and the DP4xxx
 projectors check in the Cyclops menu, Button should be set to LEFT.
<P>
<LI><B>What is included in the 2050-PC and the 2050-WS Cyclops?</B>
<P>
<TABLE BORDER=1>
	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=234>&#160<B>2050-PC</B></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=5></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=239>&#160<B>2050-WS</B></TD>
	</TR>
	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=234>&#160<EM>Drivers:</EM></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=5></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=239>&#160<EM>Drivers:</EM></TD>
	</TR>
	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=234 ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
&#160	PC Cyclops <BR>
&#160	Mac Cyclops </TD>
		<TD WIDTH=5></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=239>
&#160	PC Cyclops<BR>
&#160	Mac Cyclops<BR>
&#160	SunOS 4.1x (Solaris 1.1.1) <BR>
&#160	SunOS 5.x (Solaris 2.3) <BR>
&#160	Silicon Graphics IRIX 5.3 <BR>
&#160	Hewlett Packard HPUX 9.05 <BR>
		</TD>
	</TR>
	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=234>&#160<EM>Cables:</EM></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=5></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=239>&#160<EM>Cables:</EM></TD>
	</TR>
	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=234 ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
&#160	C927 9-pin/25-pin Adapter <BR>
&#160	C936-6 PC serial cable <BR>
&#160	C470-6 Mac ADB cable </TD>
		<TD WIDTH=5></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=239>
&#160	C927 9-pin/25-pin Adapter <BR>
&#160	C936-6 PC serial cable<BR>
&#160	C470-6 Mac ADB cable<BR>
&#160	C902-6 Mini Din serial cable <BR>
&#160	C903-6 Workstation cable </TD>
	</TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
<LI><B>Is there an upgrade option from the 2050-PC to the 2050-WS?</B>  
<P>
Yes.  The A205 upgrade kit includes the Sun, Silicon Graphics, HP drivers, manual, and workstation cables.  The kit price is $495. 
<P>
<LI><B>With the 2050 Cyclops that works with the Ovation+84X and the Ovation+920 panels, how can the menus and the LightBoard feature be accessed?</B>
<P>  
<TABLE >
	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=116><B>To Activate:</B></TD>
		<TD WIDTH=467><B>Click:</B></TD>
	</TR>

	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=116>Menu</TD>
		<TD WIDTH=467>To the right or left of the projected image</TD>
	</TR>

	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=116>LightBoard</TD>
		<TD WIDTH=467>Above the projected image</TD>
	</TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
<LI><B>Does Proxima sell a Cyclops 50-foot extension cable?</B>   
<P>
Yes, Proxima sells a Cyclops 50-foot extension serial cable, part number C941-50.  List price is $99.95.  This cable works with the Workstation, Mac and PC Cyclops cables.   
</OL>
<P>


