<HEAD>
<TITLE>Frequently Asked Questions - Remote Software</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor = "#ffffff">
<center>
<A HREF="solving.map"><IMG SRC="jpgs/header.jpg" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Support And Services"></A>
</center>
<br>
<H2>Remote Ware</H2>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<EM><H3><A NAME="pcremote">PC Remote</A></H3></EM>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<OL TYPE=1, 2, 3, ...>
<LI><B>Which Proxima units does PC Remote or Mac Remote work with?  What are the current versions 
of the remote software?</B>
<P>
PC Remote and Mac Remote work with the Ovation, Ovation+ and DP2xxx series.  The current
versions are:<P>
<TABLE BORDER=1>
	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=178 valign = top>PC Remote</TD>
		<TD WIDTH=377>3.20 (for older versions call Proxima for upgrade information)</TD>
	</TR>

	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=178 valign = top>Mac Remote</TD>
		<TD WIDTH=377>2.1.0 (for older versions call Proxima for upgrade information)</TD>
	</TR>
</TABLE>

<P>
<LI><B>Does PC Remote work with the 8300, 8400 or 5100 projectors?</B>  
<P>
No, PC Remote does not work with 8300, 8400 or 5100 projectors.
<P>
<LI><B>PC Remote is not working.</B>   
<P><OL>
<LI>Check the version number of PC Remote.  From the menu select Help and then About.  Version 3.01 (distributed in January 1995) has a known problem.  Have Proxima Technical Support send the current version to you.<P>
<LI>You cannot use PC Remote if you are using Cyclops with your projection device.  If you are using a Desktop Projector, you can disable Cyclops by holdng down the <I>Menu</I> key on the Control Panel while you turn on the power to the projector.</OL>
<P>
<LI><B>A "Panel not found" message appears while starting up PC Remote.</B>  
<P>
Check that both the video cable and the serial cable are plugged into both the panel and computer.  Check that there is an image on the panel.  
</OL>
<P> 
<HR>
<P>
<EM><H3><A NAME="macremote">Mac Remote</A></H3></EM>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<OL TYPE=1, 2, 3, ...>
<LI><B>I have a problem booting with Mac Remote.</B>   
<P>
A conflict exists with another extension.  Rename Mac Remote extension to AMACREMOTE (begins with letter A), then it will load first.
<P>
<LI><B>Does Mac Remote work with the 8300, 8400, or 5100 projectors?</B>  
<P>
No, Mac Remote does not work with 8300, 8400, or 5100 projectors.
</OL>
<P>

<center>
