<HTML>
<HEAD> 
<TITLE> Field Note: #38a </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor = "#ffffff">
<center>
<A HREF="solving.map"><IMG SRC="jpgs/header.jpg" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Support And Services"></A>
<H2>Field Note:  #38a</H2>
</center>

<P>
Date: August 26, 1996
<P>
Subject:  Sense Line Settings for Proxima Ovation+ 920/944 or
DP9100<FONT SIZE=2> </FONT>
<P>
Field Note:  #38A <I>(Replaces Field Note #38 dated February 1,
1996)<BR>
<BR>
</I>
<P>
<U><B>PROBLEM<BR></B></U>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>When connecting Macintosh computers or some workstations
to the Proxima Ovation+ 920/944 or DP9100 without a monitor or
terminator, you may not obtain the correct resolution.  When this
happens, the Sense Line settings must be used to emulate a monitor.
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<U><B>DISCUSSION<BR>
</B></U>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Some video cards rely on sense line information supplied
by the monitor to determine the signal (resolution) to output
on the video port.  When the video card does not detect the monitor
sense line information, the output signal may default to an unintended
resolution or no signal at all.  <BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>The Sense Lines Settings within the Proxima Ovation+
920/944 or DP9100 menus can be used to configure the panel to
emulate different types of monitors.  The settings are made on
the Proxima Ovation+ 920/944 or DP9100  before the system is brought
up.  With some of the Macintosh resolutions, a special terminator
is required.  Proxima recommends a programmable terminator produced
by Griffin Communications.  (Contact information for Griffin Communications
is included on page 2.)<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<U><B>SOLUTION<BR>
</B></U>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>To use the Proxima Ovation+ 920/944 or DP9100  to
project an image without connecting an external monitor, follow
these steps.</FONT>
<OL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>Connect the computer to the Proxima Ovation+
920/944 or DP9100.  Do NOT turn on the computer at this time.
 </FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>Turn on the Proxima Ovation+ 920/944 or DP9100.
 Bring the menu up.  In the Advanced Menu, configure the Sense
Line settings in accordance with the information in the table
on Page 2.  </FONT>

<LI><FONT SIZE=2>Press the Menu button to close the menu and save
the settings.</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>Without powering down the panel, turn the computer
system on.  </FONT>
</OL>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2> The image should come up in the desired resolution.
 Adjust the image with the Sync button if necessary.</FONT>
<TABLE BORDER=1>

<TR><TD WIDTH=126><B><FONT SIZE=1>System</FONT></B></TD><TD WIDTH=172><B><FONT SIZE=1>Graphic Card / Monitor Type</FONT></B>
