<TD WIDTH=61><FONT SIZE=1>Low </FONT></TD><TD WIDTH=57><FONT SIZE=1>High</FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH=59><FONT SIZE=1>Low</FONT></TD><TD WIDTH=65><FONT SIZE=1>Low</FONT>
</TD></TR>

</TABLE>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=1>NOTES:</FONT>
<P>
<SUP><FONT SIZE=1>1</FONT></SUP><FONT SIZE=1> Per Apple, the PowerBook
will only display resolutions up to 832 x 624.</FONT>
<P>
<SUP><FONT SIZE=1>2 </FONT></SUP><FONT SIZE=1> The Griffin Mac
Sync Adapter can select many different resolutions through switch
settings on the adapter itself.  Instructions to use these switches
are included with the adapter.  To contact Griffin regarding the
adapter (part number 02-20-UNV):   Griffin Communications Corporation,
1451 Elm Hill Pike, Suite 100, Nashville, TN  37210, phone (615)
399-0990, fax (615) 399-7060. </FONT>
<P>
<SUP><FONT SIZE=1>3 </FONT></SUP><FONT SIZE=1>Using sense lines
with Silicon Graphics workstations requires the use of the Proxima
C943-6 SGI 13C3 to 13C3 cable.  This cable is not included with
the Proxima Ovation+ 920, thus it is available in the Proxima
SGI Cable Accessory Kit (part no. A36.)</FONT>
