<TITLE> Field Note: #41a </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor = "#ffffff">
<center>
<A HREF="solving.map"><IMG SRC="jpgs/header.jpg" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Support And Services"></A>
<H2>Field Note:  #41a</H2>

</center>
<P>
Date: August 26, 1996
<P>
Subject:   Cyclops Drivers for Windows 95
<P>
Field Note:  #41A <I>(Replaces Field Note #41 dated December 15,
1995)<BR>
<BR>
</I>
<P>
<U><B>PROBLEM</B></U>
<P>
How to obtain the Windows 95 (v4.2) Cyclops driver.
<P>
<U><B>DISCUSSION</B></U>
<P>
A new Cyclops driver for Windows 95 and Windows 3.x has been released
and is currently available on our Internet site at http://www.prxm.com.
 <BR>

<P>
To download, choose the <I>Technical Support</I> link on the bottom
of the first Proxima web page, choose <I>Downloadable Files</I>
and then <I>Software/Drivers</I>.<BR>

<P>
If you do not have Internet access, a driver diskette is available
from Proxima Customer Service at 1-800-447-7694, option #1.  For
assistance in troubleshooting Cyclops, please contact Technical
Support at option #2. <BR>

<P>
Complete installation instructions are contained in the README.TXT
file that is included with the driver.<BR>

<P>
NOTE:  This driver will also resolve the issue of erratic mouse
movement on certain laptops using the Cyclops 3.01 driver. <BR>
<BR>
