<HEAD>
<TITLE> Resellers Forum - VIP Sales-Support Plan </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink = "AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="partnering_pc.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/partnering_header.gif" border = none width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  alt = "Resellers Forum"></A><br clear = all>
</center>

<table width = 594>
	<tr>
		<td><center><H2><font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> VIP sales-support plan</H2></center>
<B>(Computer Reseller News - March 18, 1996)</B>
<A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=LB10&sction=Description"><IMG SRC="gifs/lightbook.gif" width = 216 height = 180 align = right hspace = 9 border = none alt = "Lightbook Projector"></A>
<p>
<font size = "+1"><font color = "FF0000">PROXIMA</font> CORP. is expanding its two-tier reseller base with the unveiling of a VIP sales-support program.
<p>
The initiative seeks to cultivate partnerships between <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> and resellers by providing VARs with enhanced sales and marketing support.
<p>
The San Diego-based developer, manufacturer and marketer of desktop-projection equipment hopes to increase the number of VARs buying through distribution from 2,000 to 3,000 over the next year.  Among those distributors working with Proxima are Tech Data Corp., Ingram Micro Inc., Merisel Inc. and Access Graphics Inc.
<p>
"We want to ensure resellers are positioned to tap into this $1-billion market," said David Riberi, North American distribution sales manager for <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font>, which sells an array of LCD-projection equipment including projectors, panels and pointer systems.
<p>
The company draws two-thirds of its revenue from 60 Premier VARs that buy directly from <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font>.
<p>
But Riberi said that the two-tier channel presents a wealth of opportunity.
<p>
One goal of the program is to develop a base of 400 VIP resellers whose business would comprise 50 percent of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> revenue through the two-tier channel.
<p>
"We want to be more visible to resellers working through distribution, and we want our resellers to take a more proactive interest in us," said Riberi.
<p>
The VIP program builds on <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> existing channel program which provides distribution sales representatives who work closely with VARs to help them capture accounts; a <A HREF="free.html">free, 10-day evaluation of Proxima products</A>; and a not-for-resale demo program through which resellers can buy desktop-projection equipment at a discounted rate and rent it out or use it internally for training and presentations.
<p>
The VIP program  offers VARs dedicated sales support, customized marketing support, enhanced demo and evaluation programs, and sales incentives.
<p>
In offering dedicated sales support, the program helps resellers target customers and bolster sales pitches with a well rounded knowledge of what the competition has to  offer.</font><p></td>
	</tr>
</table>

<center>
<img src="../gifs/logo2.gif" width = 400 height = 53 alt = "Proxima - Multimedia Projectors">
