<HEAD>
<TITLE>The DP4100z and DP4200z offer astounding image quality.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_products.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/new_products_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "New Products"></A>
<p>
<H2>The Desktop Projector 4100z and Desktop<br>
Projector 4200z offer astounding image quality.</H2>
</center>

<IMG SRC="gifs/4100z.gif" align = right width = 252 height = 185 "Desktop Projector 4100z">
<font size = "+2"><B>F</B></font><font size = "+1">or important, high-profile presentations, you need a projector with unparalleled image quality. The <font color = "FF0000">Proxima&#174</font> <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP4100z&sction=Description">Desktop Projector<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup> 4100z</A> and 4200z meet this challenge and set a new standard in image quality. Based on Texas Instruments' <A HREF="newdp4100_2.html">Digital Light Processing<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup> (DLP<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup>)</A> technology, they display images that are simply astounding in their clarity, uniformity, and photo-realistic color.
<p>
The DP4100z supports VGA images, offering 315 ANSI lumens in color and 1050 ANSI lumens in grayscale. For even wider computer compatibility, the DP4200z offers true SVGA resolution. It displays 400 ANSI lumens in color and a remarkable 1400 ANSI lumens in grayscale. With a zoom lens and multiple computer, video, and audio inputs, the Desktop Projector 4100z and 4200z are ready for the most demanding multimedia presentations.
<p>
<LI>	Photo-realistic images and color suited to the highest profile presentation 
<LI>	Flexible setup and operation that support the most demanding multimedia presentations
<LI>	Optional <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=MediaExpress&sction=Description">MediaExpress<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup></A> system for presentations without the computer or the cables
<p>
<B>High performance made easy</B>
<p>
In addition to setting a new standard in image quality, the Desktop Projector 4100z and 4200z are easy to use. Connecting to your computer is truly as simple as plug and play. With built-in keystone correction and simple height adjustment, it's easy to get the best possible image in seconds. The motorized 1.5:1 zoom lens allows you to place these projectors anywhere in the room-front or back-without compromising image quality. When you need to project text-intensive or low-color applications, switch to the grayscale Workgroup mode and more than triple the brightness of your images.
<p>
The Desktop Projector 4100z and 4200z include a <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP2060/2050&sction=Description">Cyclops remote control</A> and Cyclops F/X software. This not only allows you to control the projector and the computer remotely with mouse-like precision, but you can also add transition and special effects to your presentations without going back to your computer.
<p>
<B>Presentations without the computer</B>
<p>
<A HREF="frame_adobe1.html"><IMG SRC="gifs/adobe_logo.gif" align = right border = none width = 92 height = 72 hspace = 4></A>The MediaExpress<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup> option offers an integrated electronic presentation system for your Desktop Projector 4100z or 4200z-without a computer. You can display images that were created in any software application on any system, simply by inserting a disk into the projector. The MediaExpress system is based on the Adobe&#174 Acrobat&#174 Player<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup> product and the Adobe Portable Document Format (PDF), the cross-platform standard for sharing electronic information. Using the <A HREF="frame_adobe2.html">Adobe Acrobat Exchange<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup> software</A> that is included with the MediaExpress system, you can easily create PDF files on your PC or Macintosh. Then all that you need to do is save the files on a floppy disk and insert the disk in your projector. The MediaExpress system will display your images exactly as they appeared on your computer, no matter what resolution or color. 
<p>
<center>
<table border = 4>
	<tr>
		<td align = center><font size = "+1">&#160Download a <A HREF="dp4100z.pdf"><IMG SRC="gifs/pdf_logo.gif" width = 28 height = 31 border = none></A> file of the new <A HREF="dp4100z.pdf">DP 4100z datasheet</A>! </td>
	</tr>
</table>
</center>
<p>
<B>Options to fit your style</B>
<p>
The Desktop Projector 4100z and 4200z offer other options that allow you to tailor these projectors to your presentation style. There's a hard drive version of MediaExpress that allows you to store presentations directly in the projector. The optional Cyclops&#174; interactive pointer system provides precise, point-and-click control directly from the projected image. And an optional wireless audio system provides exceptional audio quality without cables.
<p>
<B>Features</B>
<p>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="newdp4100_2.html">DLP (Digital Light Processing) technology</A> provides crisp, photo-realistic images
<LI>SVGA support (DP4200z only) for wide computer compatibility
<LI>Full multimedia capability with two computer, two video, one microphone, and four stereo audio inputs
<LI>Bright color images that more than triple in brightness in grayscale mode
<LI>Motorized 1.5:1 zoom lens for flexibility in positioning
<LI>Supports all three worldwide video standards
<LI>Optional MediaExpress image display system for electronic presentations without a computer or cables
<LI>Optional Cyclops interactive pointer system for precise, point-and-click control from the projected image
<LI>Optional wireless audio for easy setup of your sound system
</UL>
</font>
<p>

<hr width = 300>

