<HEAD>
<TITLE>The New Desktop Projector 9100!</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_products.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/new_products_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "New Products"></A>
<p>
<H2>High-resolution projection has never been as easy<br>
as with the <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Desktop Projector 9100</H2>
</center>

<IMG SRC="gifs/proj9100_closed.gif" align = right width = 280 height = 180>
<font size = "+2"><B>B</B></font><font size = "+1">RIGHT enough for use in lighted rooms, the <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Desktop Projector 9100 lets you see the "big picture" all at once.  This makes it ideal for projecting high-resolution PC and workstation images in fine detail and 24-bit color.  It is the perfect solution for visually demanding applications such as complex spreadsheets, business graphics, GIS, and CAD.  And, it's so easy to use and compact that it sets a whole new set of expectations for high-resolution projection.  The Desktop Projector 9100 supports all popular PC, Macintosh, and workstation systems.  It also provides integrated digital video and stereo audio for the finest multimedia presentations.
<p>
<B>Intelligently scales images for full-screen viewing</B>
<p>
The <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP9100&sction=Description">Desktop Projector 9100</A> is an XGA projector with a resolution of 1024 x 768 pixels. It provides full-screen viewing of high- and low-resolution computer and video images through its Fit-to-View technology. Using the Fit-to-View feature you can enlarge a 640 x 480 image to fill the entire 1024 x 768 screen. Or, you can scale down a 1280 x 1024 image for complete viewing while preserving the clarity and detail of the image. The Desktop Projector 9100 also provides true-resolution viewing with exact pixel-by-pixel representation and fast image panning of resolutions higher than 1024 x 768.
<p>
<B>Offers presentations without the computer</B>
<p>
<A HREF="frame_adobe2.html"><IMG SRC="gifs/acrobat_logo.gif" align = left border = none width = 88 height = 31 hspace = 6></A>The optional <A HREF="newmedex.html">MediaExpress</A> image display system offers an integrated electronic presentation system for your Desktop Projector 9100--without a computer. You can display images that were created in any software application on any system, simply by inserting a disk into the Desktop Projector 9100. The MediaExpress system is based on the <A HREF="frame_adobe2.html">Adobe&#174; Acrobat&#174; Player</A> product and the Adobe Portable Document Format (PDF), the cross-platform standard for sharing electronic information. Using the Adobe Acrobat Exchange software that is included with the MediaExpress system, you can easily create PDF files on your PC, Macintosh or workstation. Then all that you need to do is save the files on a floppy disk and insert the disk in your Desktop Projector 9100. The MediaExpress system will display your images exactly as they appeared on your computer, no matter what resolution or color. 
<p>
<center>
<table border = 4>
	<tr>
		<td align = center><font size = "+1">&#160Download a <A HREF="dp9100.pdf"><IMG SRC="gifs/pdf_logo.gif" width = 28 height = 31 border = none></A> file of the new <A HREF="dp9100.pdf">DP 9100 datasheet</A>! </td>
	</tr>
</table>
</center>
<p>
<B>Provides cordless mouse control from projected image</B>
<p>
The Desktop Projector 9100 includes a <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP2060/2050&sction=Description">Cyclops&#174; remote control</A> with Cyclops F/X software for cordless mouse control. For even more flexibility, you can add the optional Cyclops interactive pointer system. This give you precise, point-and-click control of your computer and your Desktop Projector 9100 directly from the projected image. 
<p>
<B>Features</B>
<p>
<UL>
<LI>Support of all popular PC, Macintosh, and workstation systems including Sun, HP, and SGI
<LI>Bright 300 ANSI lumen (typical) projected image accommodates most lighting conditions
<LI>Fit-to-View technology for full-screen and full-resolution viewing of images from 640 x 480 to 1280 x 1024 resolutions
<LI>Outstanding image quality with uniform corner-to-corner illumination
<LI>Excellent portability with the smallest form factor of all high-resolution, active-matrix projectors
<LI>Includes Cyclops remote control and Cyclops F/X software for mouse-like control of projector and computer including zoom and other special presentation effects
<LI>Includes LightBoard drawing tool for highlighting and drawing on the projected image
<LI>Optional MediaExpress image display system for electronic presentations without a computer or cables
<LI>Optional Cyclops interactive pointer system for precise, point-and-click control from the projected image
</UL>
<p>
<B>The DP 9100 offers plug-and-play setup and high resolution projection</B>
<p>
<table border = 3>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><IMG SRC="gifs/proj9100.gif" align = left width = 147 height = 180></td>
		<td>Two integrated stereo speakers face the audience for best sound quality in multimedia presentations.
<p>
Clear Screen feature provides for transparency projection.
<p>
Flip mirror for easy placement of image on screen.
<p>
Easy access to controls from the projector with intuitive menu and quick setup.
<p>
Optional Cyclops for point-and-click control of computer and projector from projected image.
<p>
Compact, rugged design and self-protecting optics make it easy to carry along with you.
<p>
Optional MediaExpress image display system for presenting without the computer.</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<p>
<B>DP 9100 Applications</B>
<p>
The Desktop Projector 9100 is the perfect solution for demanding high-resolution projection. It offers premium performance for training sessions and workgroups as well as for formal presentations. The Fit-to-View feature displays the entire image--or the "big picture"--all at once, while still providing the ability to show the fine details of that same image. This makes it ideal for projecting CAD/CAM, GIS, command and control, and business graphics images. Imagine how much productivity will improve when the audience can see the entire spreadsheet or solid modeling rendering. What better way to demonstrate software capabilities or train new users than to communicate important concepts to an entire audience from one complete view. The Desktop Projector 9100's intelligent scaling capability projects even the most detailed workstation CAD image with clarity, making it perfect for design reviews or client presentations. And, the compact, rugged design of the Desktop Projector 9100 is a natural fit with portable command and control applications.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀

<p>

