<HEAD>
<TITLE>Proxima Reports Third Quarter Results for Fiscal 1997</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">
<table width = 596>
	<tr>
		<td>
<center>
<A HREF="hot_releases.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/press_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Press Releases"></A>
<p>
<H2><font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation Reports Third<br>Quarter Results for Fiscal 1997</H2>
</center>

<font size = "+1">SAN DIEGO -- January 20, 1997 -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), today reported net income of $1,838,000, or 25 cents per share, for the three months ended December 31, 1996, compared with net income of $3,229,000, or 46 cents per share, in the same period last   
year. Revenue for the third quarter of fiscal 1997 increased to $47,365,000 from $44,216,000 in the third quarter of fiscal 1996.
<p>
For the first nine months of fiscal 1997, <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> reported a net loss of $1,693,000, or 24 cents per share, on revenues of $118,625,000 compared with net income of $6,232,000, or 89 cents per share, on revenues of $112,206,000 during the first nine months of the previous fiscal year.
<p>
The Company's earnings performance improved during the third quarter over the second quarter primarily due to a strong ramp-up in sales of the Company's new SVGA multimedia projectors. In addition, shipments of backlog which existed at the beginning of the third quarter positively impacted the quarter's results. Gross margins came in at 29 percent for the third quarter. Actual operating expenses of $11.2 million were essentially flat compared to the second quarter which was consistent with the Company's goal to keep expenses flat with the levels set in the fourth quarter of fiscal 1996. However, as a percentage of revenue, operating expenses dropped to 23.6 percent compared with 30.2 percent in the second quarter.
<p>
Cash and short-term investments increased to $19.0 million compared with   
$17.6 million at September 30, 1996. Accounts receivable increased by $12 million and accounts payable also increased $12 million relative to last quarter. The increase in accounts receivable was due to a higher amount of sales generated during the last half of the quarter. The increase in accounts payable was due primarily to large inventory receipts during the month of December that were not yet paid.
<p>
Inventories rose $3.2 million to $27.4 million in the quarter compared with $24.2 million at September 30, 1996, primarily due to an increase in the inventory levels of sourced Desktop Projectors and components for the Lightbook family.
<p>
"As we expected, demand for SVGA multimedia projectors was strong and represented a significant percentage of our total sales during the quarter ended December 31, 1996," said John Rehfeld, president and chief executive officer of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font>. Mr. Rehfeld continued, "<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> was one of the first companies to deliver a true SVGA resolution multimedia projector using polysilicon technology. While we believe that the market for SVGA projectors will experience strong growth, we expect that most of our major competitors will introduce and deliver competitive SVGA products within the next three or four months. With the entry of these new projectors, we expect that price competition will intensify and that our gross margin percentage will trend lower than the 29 percent recorded in the third quarter of fiscal 1997." Mr. Rehfeld also indicated that XGA resolution projectors were beginning to gain market acceptance and that the Company's DP9100 XGA projector was a solid margin contributor during the third quarter.
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of multimedia projection products which bring the power of the computer to the workgroup. These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.</font>
<p>
<center>    <B># # #</B>   </center>
<p>
Important notice:  This press release contains forward- looking statements   
relating to future demand of SVGA multimedia projectors, operating expense goals, gross margins, and the market acceptance of XGA projectors. Actual results could differ materially from those projected in the forward-looking statements as a result of risk factors such as: short product lives, technological shifts, potential technical difficulties (including component/product availability from suppliers) that could substantially delay products at any time, competition (including new and directly competitive products from others), continued downward pricing pressures, demand fluctuations, and the uncertainty of market acceptance of products by both distributors and end-user customers. Further, given the foregoing risks, the Company makes no   
assurance regarding the future success of any of its products. Revenues and earnings in the prior quarter are not an accurate predictor of future results. The Company does not project future financial results and expressly disclaims any responsibility for any such projections released by third party analysts. Investors are strongly encouraged to review the risk factors set forth in the Company's last filed Forms 10-K and 10-Q.
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a registered trademark of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation.  Desktop Projector is a trademark of Proxima 
Corporation.  Digital Flipchart is a trademark of Tegrity, Inc. All other trademarks and registered trademarks are property of their respective owners.
