<HEAD>
<TITLE>Proxima Introduces New Meeting Room Solutions</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_releases.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/press_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Press Releases"></A>
<p>
<H2><font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Introduces New Meeting 
Room Solutions</H2>
<H3>Enhances Meeting Effectiveness with the Tegrity Digital Flipchart</H3>
</center>

<font size = "+1">SAN DIEGO -- November 11, 1996 -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), a leader in the multimedia projection market, today announced the <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> meeting room solution, featuring the <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DFC1N&sction=Description">Tegrity Digital Flipchart<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup></A>.  The new solution revolutionizes work sessions by providing capabilities for capturing decisions, sharing ideas and distributing plans and action items -- creating interactive, productive meetings.
<p>
This innovative solution is a combination of select <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> <A HREF="../Solutions/solutions.html">multimedia projectors</A> and the Tegrity Digital Flipchart, which includes Tegrity's patented Visual Interaction<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup> software, a video camera and video capture card.  The meeting room solution projects a virtual touch panel onto any white surface, which allows you to annotate images and capture anything written on the surface.  This solution records everything from whiteboard brainstorming sessions, marked-up computer documents and annotated video clips.
<p>
"Almost every working session involves the manipulation of various types of information from many multimedia sources," said John Rehfeld, <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> president and CEO.  "This joint solution from <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> and Tegrity eliminates administrative headaches and drives participant action and follow-up through an interactive environment."
<p>
By eliminating the need for detailed note-taking, the meeting room solution increases retention and participation while decreasing miscommunication of action items and decisions.  The meeting information is recorded, and can then be distributed to participants via printing, e-mailing, faxing, or posting to the Internet or company intranet.  In addition, the software furnishes predefined forms, such as Meeting Summary, Agenda, Action Items and Decisions for business meetings.
<p>
"Our patented technology enables anyone to operate Digital Flipchart with great ease.  The meeting room solution is easy to use and is as portable as a paper flipchart," said Daniel Platzker, president and CEO of Tegrity.  "<font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> state-of-the-art projection technology effectively complements our application software to meet the needs of the new interactive meeting market segment."
<p>
The Tegrity Digital Flipchart runs on a Pentium-based PC running the Windows<sup><font size = "-1">&#174;</font></sup> 95 operating systems.  Files created with the solution can be viewed and edited on Windows 3.1 or higher, and by a Web browser from virtually any system including Macintosh and UNIX workstations. The meeting room solution is available with many of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> <A HREF="../Solutions/solutions.html">multimedia projectors</A>, including the <A HREF="newlightbook.html">Lightbook<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup> mobile projector</A> and Desktop Projectors <A HREF="newdp4100z.html">4100</A>, <A HREF="newdp4100z.html">4200</A>, <A HREF="newdp5500.html">5500</A> and <A HREF="newdp5600.html">5600</A>.  Available in November 1996 through authorized resellers and computer products dealers, customers will save $500 when they purchase a <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> projector and the Tegrity Digital Flipchart  together.  <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> multimedia projectors start at $4,999, and the Tegrity Digital Flipchart  begins at $2,495.  All prices are U.S. suggested retail.  For more information please contact <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation at (800) 447-7692.
<p>
The two companies will demonstrate the new meeting room solution at the Fall Comdex Show in Las Vegas, November 18-22, at the <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> booth (#M428, Sands Convention Center).
<p>
<B>About Tegrity, Inc.</B>
<p>
Founded in 1994, <A HREF="http://www.tegrity.com">Tegrity, Inc.</A> develops and markets software that dramatically simplifies people-computer interaction specifically in the area of group settings.  The Tegrity Digital Flipchart is an innovative productivity tool for any meeting and classroom that allows anyone to easily organize, document and distribute meeting information.  Tegrity is headquartered in San Jose, California.
<p>
<B>About <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation</B>
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of multimedia projection products that bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.  The company's headquarters are in San   
Diego, California.</font>
<p>
<center>    <B># # #</B>   </center>
<p>
Important notice:  This press release contains forward-looking statements   
relating to a new product, and its benefits, availability date and general market demand.  Actual results could differ materially from those projected in the forward-looking statements as a result of risk factors such as: short product lives, technological shifts, current technical issues that can't be resolved on a timely basis and other potential technical difficulties (including component/product availability from suppliers) that could substantially delay the new product, competition (including new and directly competitive products from others), pricing pressures, incorrect assumptions regarding market demand, and the significant uncertainty of market acceptance of new products by both distributors and end-user customers.  Investors are strongly encouraged to review the risk factors set forth in the Company's last filed Forms 10-K and 10-Q.
