<HEAD>
<TITLE>Proxima Announces Alliance with Diba Inc.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_releases.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/press_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Press Releases"></A>
<p>
<H2><font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Offers True SVGA 
Polysilicon Projector</H2>
<H3>Lightweight Desktop Projector 5600 Leads the Industry in Brightness</H3>
</center>

<font size = "+1">SAN DIEGO -- November 11, 1996 -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), a leader in projection technology, today announced the <A HREF="newdp5600.html">Desktop Projector 5600</A> (DP5600), one of the first true SVGA polysilicon projectors available.
<p>
The new projector offers industry-leading brightness at 500 ANSI lumens, making it an excellent choice for presentations to large groups, even in brightly lit rooms.  SVGA capability provides the resolution needed for effective projection of complex spreadsheets, business graphics and photographs.  The projector is also compatible with all domestic and international video standards (NTSC, PAL, SECAM and S-Video), and supports both IBM and Macintosh platforms.
<p>
"The DP5600 fills the demand for true SVGA resolution at 800 x 600 pixels," said John Rehfeld, president and chief executive officer of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font>.  "Combine that with superior brightness and 16.5-pound weight, and presenters now have a road-worthy projector that will deliver high quality images."
<p>
SVGA resolution (800 x 600 pixels) is standard, and VGA and XGA resolutions are also supported for maximum compatibility.  Stereo audio is supported for both computer and video presentations, with internal speakers and a volume-controlled line level output.  A separate connector is provided for microphone input, which has its own independent volume control.
<p>
Available through <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> authorized resellers, the DP5600 sells for a suggested retail price of $9,999.  For more information please contact <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> at (800) 447-7692. <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of multimedia projection products that bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.  The company's headquarters are in San   
Diego, California.</font>
<p>
<center>    <B># # #</B>   </center>
<p>
Important notice:  The company makes no assurances regarding the future   
success of its new products or the accuracy of estimated availability   
dates of said products due to risks including: short product lives,   
technological shifts, technical difficulties (including component/product   
availability from suppliers) that could substantially delay new products   
at any time, competition (including new and directly competitive products   
from others), pricing pressures, and the uncertainty of market acceptance   
of new products by both distributors and end-user customers.  Investors   
are strongly encouraged to review the risk factors set forth in the   
Company's last filed Forms 10-K and 10-Q.
