<center>
<H2><font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation Announces<br>Technology Alliance With Diba Inc.</H2>
<H3>Paves the way for Internet-enabled Multimedia Projectors</H3>
</center>

<font size = "+1">SAN DIEGO, California, October 30, 1996 -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), a leader in the multimedia projection market, Wednesday announced a technology alliance with <A HREF="frame_diba.html">Diba, Inc.</A>, the leading Information Appliance technology provider.
<p>
The alliance expects to combine <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> <A HREF="../Solutions/solutions.html">multimedia projectors</A> with technologies from Diba that enable Internet and Intranet access and browsing.  The two companies will demonstrate this technology at the Fall <A HREF="where.html">COMDEX</A> Show in Las Vegas, November 18-22, at the <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Booth No. M428 (Sands Convention Center).
<p>
"By entering into a joint development effort with a technology expert such as Diba, <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> goal is to create a true meeting room appliance which will allow a rich media display and provide access to information sources via the Internet," said John Rehfeld, <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> president and chief executive officer.
<p>
"This technology solution should directly benefit our corporate, education and government customers, whose interests lie in ease of use, convenience, and affordability." "We are pleased to team up with a world leader in multimedia projectors to prove the versatility of Information Appliance technology," said   
Farzad Dibachi, president and chief executive officer of Diba.
<p>
<B>About Diba</B>
<p>
<A HREF="frame_diba.html">Diba</A> is the leading technology supplier for the Information Appliance marketplace.  Based in Menlo Park, Calif., Diba is dedicated to making information more accessible to more people.  Diba and its partners are creating a diverse family of Information Appliances. Diba-based Information Appliances include devices for sending and receiving electronic mail, Internet access from standard televisions and multimedia projectors, and a wide range of specialized appliances for the telephony, financial services, and healthcare industries.
<p>
<B>About <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font></B>
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of multimedia projection products that bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.  The company's headquarters are in San Diego, California.</font>
<p>
This news release contains forward-looking statements relating to a technology alliance, future products and the potential benefits of future products.  Actual results could differ materially from those projected in the forward-looking statements as a result of risk factors such as: technological shifts, current technical issues that can't be resolved on a timely basis and other potential technical difficulties (including component/product availability from suppliers) that could substantially delay future products, competition (including new and directly competitive products from others), pricing pressures, and the uncertainty of market acceptance of future products by both distributors and end-user customers.  The Company makes no assurances regarding the success of future products, or their availability date, if ever.  Investors are strongly encouraged to review the risk factors set forth in the Company's last filed Forms 10-K and 10-Q.
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a registered trademark of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation.  All other trademarks and registered trademarks are the property of their respective   
owners.
<p>

