<center>
<H2><font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Announces the Lightbook Projector</H2>
<H3>Provides the first multimedia notebook projector built for the road</H3>
</center>

<font size = "+1">SAN DIEGO, California, October 15, 1996 -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), a leader in the mobile projection market, today announced the <A HREF="newlightbook.html">Lightbook projector</A> -- the industry's first lightweight, multimedia notebook projector built specifically to withstand the rigors of the road.  The Lightbook projector combines a compact, rugged design with best-in-class functionality to provide the ideal solution for the new breed of mobile professional, according to John Rehfeld, <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> chief executive officer.
<p>
"Today's top sales professionals realize the importance technology plays in getting and keeping a competitive advantage.  Good presentation skills are no longer enough to close a deal," Rehfeld said.  "When combined with a laptop computer, the Lightbook projector provides great image quality to turn a good presentation into a winning presentation."  Rehfeld said that while the Lightbook projector was designed to facilitate on-the-road selling, it is also very appropriate for meetings, lectures, and training venues.  Potential users include software salespeople, advertising and public relations agencies, marketing and sales professionals, high-level speakers and trainers, and mobile executives.  "Basically, no matter what business you're in, <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is your partner for success in on-the-road presentations," said Rehfeld.
<p>
A true multimedia tool, the Lightbook projector provides plug-and-play SVGA image support and handles integrated video with direct connection of a VCR, laser disk, or any other video source.  The Lightbook projector stands alone in terms of durability and portability.  The rugged projector, featuring a full-metal chassis, weighs about 11 pounds, and is small enough to fit inside a small attache case or under an airline seat.  Full presentation and projector control are provided via the <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Cyclops remote control, which allows users to open files, click on hot buttons, and perform any other mouse action from anywhere in the room; combined with Cyclops F/X software, which enhances presentations with a variety of special effects.  The Lightbook projector's flexible design supports both PC and Macintosh computers, and every Lightbook projector comes ready for worldwide use with an autoswitching power supply for U.S. or European electrical outlets.
<p>
The Lightbook projector will be available through <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> authorized resellers, and sells for a suggested retail price of $4,999.  For more information please contact <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation at (800) 447-7692.
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of multimedia projection products that bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.  The company's headquarters are in San Diego, California.</font>
<p>

