<center>
<H2><font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Provides Desktop Projectors<br>to Republican National Convention</H2>
</center>

SAN DIEGO, California,  August 5, 1996 -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), today announced the company donated two <A HREF="newdp5500.html">Desktop Projector  5500</A> (DP5500) LCD multimedia projectors to the 1996 Republican National Convention for use by headquarters personnel, and on-site at the San Diego Convention Center during the convention here August 12-15.
<p>
According to William I. Greener III, Convention Manager, Republican   
National Convention personnel will use the projectors to integrate   
multimedia, support training, assist in office automation, and enhance   
presentations and videoconferencing as part of their overall convention   
support programs.  "We are very pleased and excited that one of San   
Diego's leading high technology companies was able to provide their   
products for our administrative support efforts," Greener said.   
<p>
"<font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> projectors will allow us to incorporate graphics, text, photographs, animation, live video and sound to enhance communications in all our conferences, large and small."
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> DP5500, recently announced in June 1996, offers multimedia customers the brightest polysilicon projector on the market (500 ANSI lumens).  Because the DP5500 offers incredibly bright, fully saturated images measuring up to 30 feet diagonally, it can be used to make clear presentations before larger audiences than previously possible with similar projectors.
<p>
The DP5500 includes two independent computer inputs (PC and/or Mac) and   
two independent video inputs, making it simple to connect multiple   
presenters.  It also is designed to make controlling a presentation   
easier.  The DP5500 features a remote control with zoom and focus   
buttons, as well as a "joystick" that provides mouse-like control of a   
PC-compatible computer.  Additional, the DP5500 can handle SVGA (800x600)   
computer images.
<p>
The DP5500 includes as an option <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP2060/2050&sction=Description">Cyclops interactive pointer system</A>, which allows precise point-and-click cordless mouse control of the computer.  The Cyclops system is designed to facilitate better interaction between the presenter and the audience.  The DP5500 is multimedia ready and compatible with all domestic and international video standards (NTSC, PAL and SECAM), as well as S-Video.
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of multimedia projection products that bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.  The company's headquarters are in San   
Diego, California.  Contact <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> at 800-447-7692 or on the World Wide Web, http://www.prxm.com.
<p>

