<HEAD>
<TITLE>PROXIMA CORPORATION EXPECTS FIRST QUARTER LOSS</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_releases.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/press_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Press Releases"></A>
</center>

<table width = 100%>
	<tr>
		<td align = right>For more information contact:<br>
Carol Foster, The Townsend Agency<br>
(619) 457-4888<br>
or<br>
Todd Savitt, Investor Relations<br>
(619) 457-5500 x1208<br></td>
	</tr>
</table>

<center>
<H2><font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation Expects First Quarter Loss</H2>
<H3>Six Recently Introduced Products Will Be Shown at INFOCOMM</H3>
</center>

SAN DIEGO -- June 4, 1996 -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), expects that revenues and net earnings for its first quarter ending June 30, 1996 will be below earlier expectations.
<p>
"The transition and repositioning of our new and existing products are   
impacting sales and earnings more than we had previously expected.  We   
are having difficulty maintaining the momentum of our older products   
while new products are being introduced by both <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> and our competition,"  said John Rehfeld, president and chief executive officer of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font>.
<p>
"While we expressed concerns about first quarter performance in our   
<A HREF="press6.html">April 23, 1996 press release</A>, indications now are that revenues could be slightly less than in the same period last year with a loss per share of 25 to 30 cents from operations."  Rehfeld continued, "The timeliness of our new product deliveries is of the utmost importance.  The new products introduced during the first half of our fiscal year are expected to account for over 85 percent of our sales during the second half."  
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> yesterday announced three new products, including the 500 lumen <A HREF="newdp5500.html">Desktop Projector 5500</A>,  the industry's brightest polysilicon-based multimedia projector and the <A HREF="newdp9100.html">Desktop Projector 9100</A>, a compact high-resolution workstation projector.  In addition, the <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> <A HREF="newova944.html">Ovation+ 944</A>, a high-resolution LCD panel, was introduced.  Rehfeld stated,  "These new products along with the recently introduced <A HREF="newdp4100z.html">DP4100z</A>, <A HREF="newdp2910.html">DP2910</A>, and <A HREF="newmedex.html">MediaExpress</A> will be shown next week at INFOCOMM, our most important trade event which will be held at the Pennsylvania Convention Center in Philadelphia.  We have already begun shipping the DP4100 and the DP2910 in limited quantities and expect to begin shipping the other products this month, with the exception of the DP9100 which will begin shipping during the second fiscal quarter."
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of multimedia projection products which bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.
<p>

<center>     <B>#  #  #</B>    </center>

<p>
Proxima and MediaExpress are registered trademarks of Proxima Corporation.
<p>
Desktop Projector is a trademark of Proxima Corporation.
<p>
All other trademarks and registered trademarks are the property of their   
respective owners.
