<HEAD>
<TITLE>NEW DP5500 IS BRIGHTEST IN ITS CLASS</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_releases.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/press_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Press Releases"></A>
</center>

<table width = 100%>
	<tr>
		<td align = right>For more information contact:<br>
Carol Foster, The Townsend Agency<br>
(619) 457-4888<br>
or<br>
Gerald Hansen, Proxima Corporation<br>
(619) 457-5500<br></td>
	</tr>
</table>

<center>
<H2>New <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Desktop Projector 5500
<br>is brightest in its Class</H2>
<H3>500-ANSI-Lumen Brightness Eliminates<br>
Image Washout in Well-Lit Rooms</H3>
</center>

<A HREF="frame_adobe1.html"><IMG SRC="gifs/adobe_logo.gif" align = right border = none width = 92 height = 72 hspace = 4></A>SAN DIEGO -- June 3, 1996 -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), a leader in projection technology, today announced the launch of its new <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP5500&sction=Description">Desktop Projector<sup><font size = "-2">TM</font></sup> 5500</A> (DP5500), which offers multimedia customers the brightest polysilicon projector on the market (500 ANSI lumens).  Because the DP5500 is able to offer incredibly bright, fully saturated  images that measure up to 30 feet diagonally, it can be used to make clear presentations before larger audiences than previously possible with similar desktop projectors.
<p>
According to Gerald Hansen, <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> product marketing manager, "The DP5500 takes us to the next level of product performance with two new features not available on our DP5100 model.  First, we've boosted its brightness by 150 ANSI lumens over the previous model, and now we are also able to offer precise, point-and-click control through <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> Cyclops&#174 interactive pointer system."  In practical terms, Hansen said, "With the DP5500, you will never have to worry about lighting conditions in very bright rooms, and since the colors remain fully-saturated and exceptionally sharp at up to 30 diagonal feet, even the biggest images do not appear washed out, faded, or fuzzy."
<p>
The DP5500 includes two independent computer inputs (PC and/or Mac) and two independent video inputs, making it simple to connect multiple   
presenters.  It also is designed to make controlling a presentation   
easier. The DP5500 features a remote control with zoom and focus buttons, as well as a "joystick" that provides mouse-like control of a   
PC-compatible computer.  "This projector is especially flexible," says   
Hansen, "for users who want to take advantage of the 1.6:1 range of the motorized zoom lens, which makes it the widest of any projector lens in its class.  It allows you to position the projector anywhere in the room."  Additionally, the DP5500 can handle SVGA (800x600) computer images.
<p>
The DP5500 includes as an option <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> Cyclops&#174 interactive pointer system, which allows precise point-and-click cordless mouse control of the computer.  The Cyclops system is designed to facilitate better interaction between the presenter and the audience.  The DP5500 is multimedia ready and compatible with all domestic and international video standards (NTSC, PAL and SECAM), as well as S-Video.
<p>
Available through <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> authorized resellers, the Desktop Projector 5500 sells for a U.S. suggested retail price of $9,195.  For more information please contact <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation at 619/457-5500.  <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> will unveil the DP5500 at the COMDEX Spring show in Chicago (June 3 through June 6), booth number M4130.
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer, and marketer of Desktop  Projection products that bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training and computer-based presentations.  The company's headquarters are in San   
Diego, California.
<P>

<center>     <B>#  #  #</B>    </center>

<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font>and Cyclops are registered trademarks of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation.
<p>
Desktop Projector is a trademark of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation.
<p>
All other trademarks and registered trademarks are the property of their   
respective owners.
