<HEAD>
<TITLE>Portable Ovation+ 944 Illuminates the Details</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_releases.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/press_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Press Releases"></A>
</center>

<table width = 100%>
	<tr>
		<td align = right>For more information contact:<br>
Carol Foster, The Townsend Agency<br>
(619) 457-4888<br>
or<br>
Christine Jorgensen, Proxima Corporation<br>
(619) 457-5500<br></td>
	</tr>
</table>

<center>
<H2><font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation Announces PC- and Workstation-<br>Compatible, High-Resolution Projection Panel</H2>
<H3>Portable <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Ovation+ 944 Illuminates the Details</H3>
</center>

SAN DIEGO -- June 3, 1996 -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), a leader in projection technology, today announced availability of the <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Ovation&#174;+ 944 -- a very bright, workstation-compatible, active-matrix LCD projection panel capable of displaying up to 1280x1024 resolution images.  The <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Ovation+ 944's lightweight yet rugged construction and support for popular PC, Macintosh and workstation platforms make it the ideal solution for applications that require portability and high-resolution projection.
<p>
"The <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=944&sction=Description">Ovation+ 944</A> lets viewers see the big picture in bright, 24-bit color.  It is ideal for projecting visually demanding CAD, GIS, command and control, and business graphic images in vibrant detail," said Michael Chaffin, <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> chief operating officer.
<p>
In addition to high brightness, the <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Ovation+ 944 features <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> innovative Fit-toView(tm) and zoom capabilities.  The Fit-to-View feature provides full screen display of images ranging from 640x480 all the way up to 1280x1024.  The Fit-to-View feature scales images to fit within the XGA resolution (1024x768 pixels) of the LCD panel, while preserving image quality.  Integrated audio-out, via external speaker connectors, is also available for stereo sound.  The <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Ovation+ 944 also includes a high-speed data rate for full engineering workstation (EWS) support, an advanced graphical user interface, and an integrated digital video processor that decodes NTSC, PAL, and SECAM -- the three worldwide video standards -- as well as S-Video.  For added convenience, the company's unique LightBoard(tm) feature lets users draw right on the image.  The new panel is also compatible with <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP2060/2050&sction=Description">Cyclops&#174;</A> interactive pointer system, which allows precise point-and-click cordless mouse control of  a PC or workstation.
<p>
Available through <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> authorized resellers, the <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Ovation+ 944 sells for a suggested retail price of $8,495 U.S.  For more information please contact <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation at 619/457-5500.
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of Desktop Projection products that bring the power of the computer to the   
workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of   
business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.  The company's headquarters are in San Diego, California.
<p>

<center>     <B>#  #  #</B>    </center>

<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> and Cyclops are registered trademarks of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation.
<p>
Desktop Projector is a trademark of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation.
<p>
All other trademarks and registered trademarks are the property of their   
respective owners.
