<HEAD>
<TITLE>Desktop Projector 9100 Projects Fine Detail</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_releases.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/press_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Press Releases"></A>
</center>

<table width = 100%>
	<tr>
		<td align = right>For more information contact:<br>
Carol Foster, The Townsend Agency<br>
(619) 457-4888<br>
or<br>
Christine Jorgensen, Proxima Corporation<br>
(619) 457-5500<br></td>
	</tr>
</table>

<center>
<H2>WORLD'S SMALLEST, BRIGHTEST ACTIVE-MATRIX<BR>HIGH-RES PROJECTOR NOW AVAILABLE FROM <font color = "FF0000">PROXIMA</font></H2>
<H3>Desktop Projector 9100 Projects Fine Detail and Brilliant, 24-Bit Color</H3>
</center>

SAN DIEGO -- June 3, 1996 -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), a leader in projection technology, today announced the latest member of its Desktop Projector family -- the <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP9100&sction=Description">Desktop Projector 9100</A>.   Designed for visually demanding applications such as complex spreadsheets, business graphics, GIS and CAD, the new projector supports all popular PC, Macintosh, and workstation systems.  
<p>
According to Michael Chaffin, chief operating officer at <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font>, "The DP9100 is so easy to use and to travel with that it sets a whole new set of expectations for high-resolution projection.  And the viewing features are unprecedented, both in terms of true-resolution viewing and full-image viewing."  Full-image viewing of all resolutions of computer and video images is accomplished through <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> Fit-to-View technology, which can enlarge a VGA 640x480 image to fill the entire XGA 1024x768 screen.  It can also intelligently scale down a 1280x1024 image for complete viewing without sacrificing the integrity of the data.  And true-resolution viewing, with exact pixel-by-pixel representation and fast image panning, is available for resolutions higher than 1024x768.
<p>
The optional <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=MediaExpress&sction=Description">MediaExpress</A> feature provides an integrated electronic presentation system without a computer.  By simply inserting a 3.5-inch PC formatted floppy into the DP9100, users can display images created in any software application on any system. And on the DP9100, images created on a VGA system are automatically rendered at XGA resolution on the projector. MediaExpress is based on the Adobe&#174; Acrobat&#174; Player product and Adobe's Portable Document Format (PDF), the cross-platform standard for sharing electronic information.
<p>
The Desktop Projector 9100 includes as an option <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> Cyclops&#174; interactive pointer system, which allows precise point-and-click cordless mouse control of a PC or workstation.  The <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP2060/2050&sction=Description">Cyclops</A> system is designed to facilitate better interaction between the presenter and the audience.  "Making eye contact with the audience and taking advantage of other non-verbal cues is easier when the presenter is able to interact freely with the audience," Chaffin said.  "In providing that capability, the Cyclops system becomes a part of a total, integrated solution for desktop projection technology."  The Cyclops pointer system is supported on PC, Macintosh, Sun, SGI and HP platforms.  In addition, the DP9100 comes with a Cyclops multifunction remote and Cyclops F/X software for controlling the projector's controls and the presentation, as well as <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> LightBoard drawing tools for on-screen annotation.  The DP9100 is also multimedia ready, compatible with all domestic and international video standards (NTSC, PAL and SECAM), as well as S-Video, and has two rear-facing stereo speakers.
<p>
Available mid-summer through <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> authorized resellers, the Desktop Projector 9100 sells for a suggested retail price of $16,995.  For more information please contact <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation at 619/457-5500.
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of Desktop Projection products that bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training and computer-based presentations.  The company's headquarters are in San Diego, California.
<p>

<center>     <B>#  #  #</B>    </center>

<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima and</font> Cyclops are registered trademarks of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation.  Desktop Projector, Fit-to-View, LightBoard and MediaExpress are trademarks of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation.  Adobe and Acrobat are registered trademarks of Adobe Systems Incorporated.  Acrobat Exchange and Acrobat Player are trademarks of Adobe Systems Incorporated.  All other trademarks and registered trademarks are the property of their respective owners.
<p>
