<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>MediaExpress Delivers Cross-Platform, Cross-Application, Worry-Free Projection</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_releases.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/press_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Press Releases"></A>
</center>

<table width = 100%>
	<tr>
		<td align = right>For more information contact:<br>
Carol Foster, The Townsend Agency<br>
(619) 457-4888<br>
or<br>
Terry Hicks, Proxima Corporation<br>
(619) 457-5500<br></td>
	</tr>
</table>

<center>
<H2>
<font color = "FF0000">PROXIMA'S</font> SETS NEW STANDARD FOR EASE OF<br> USE WITH  REVOLUTIONARY MEDIAEXPRESS<br> PRESENTATION SYSTEM</H2>
<H3>MediaExpress with Adobe Acrobat Player Delivers 
Cross-Platform, Cross-Application, Worry-Free Projection</H3>
</center>

SAN DIEGO -- (May 15, 1996) -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), today set a new standard for ease of use in electronic presentations with the announcement of its revolutionary <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=MediaExpress&sction=Description">MediaExpress</A> worry-free presentation system.  The first standalone electronic presentation system to incorporate <A HREF="frame_adobe1.html">Acrobat Player technology</A> from Adobe Systems, Incorporated, MediaExpress provides cross-platform, cross-application, plug-and-play projection for large-screen, interactive presentations and workgroup sessions.
<p>
"MediaExpress is revolutionary in that it simplifies both the creation and delivery of electronic information," said Terry Hicks, product line manager.   "It lets you use your favorite software and any computer platform to create your presentation, then allows you to make that presentation without a computer--or even any cables to fuss with other than the power cord--merely by inserting your disk in the projector."  
<p>
Designed to work with <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> new digital light processing <A HREF="newdp4100z.html">Desktop Projector 4100z</A>, MediaExpress will ultimately be available as an option on several <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> desktop projection products.  The completely portable system lets users project documents based on the Adobe Portable Document Format (PDF), a universal file format that preserves the fidelity of visually rich information across computer platforms regardless of resolution, color depth, or the fonts used.
<p>
<center>
<table border = 4>
	<tr>
		<td align = center><font size = "+1">&#160Download a colorful <A HREF="medexpr.pdf"><IMG SRC="gifs/pdf_logo.gif" width = 28 height = 31 border = none></A> file of this <A HREF="medexpr.pdf">Press Release</A>. </td>
	</tr>
</table>
</center>
<p>
<B>Simple as Printing</B>
<p>
The MediaExpress system works with any computer or application software that can be saved to a PDF file.  Tools for creating PDF files are included in <A HREF="frame_adobe2.html">Adobe Acrobat Exchange software</A>, which comes with the MediaExpress system.  According to Hicks, the procedure for saving a PDF file is as simple as printing a document.  "With Adobe Acrobat software resident on your computer, you simply create your document and save it as a PDF file by hitting 'print' on your file menu," he explained.  "Once you've copied your document onto a disk, you then insert the disk into the projector and the Adobe Acrobat rendering engine that resides within MediaExpress opens and plays it back.  
<p>
"Within seconds," he added, "you are displaying your message using rich text and graphics from your favorite PC or Mac application.  Users thus are assured of worry-free support for a wide range of resolutions and projection applications."     
<p>
In addition, unlike existing presentation systems, which are tied to specific software packages, MediaExpress is not limited in the kinds of information it can display.  Because it is compatible with any software or hardware platform, users can incorporate content created with virtually any software package.
<p>
<B>Content Flexibility</B> 
<p>
But the ability to create presentations on any software is only part of the story.  As Hicks explained, "you can even add content later from any PDF file, add links and transitions, as well as rearrange slides.  This gives you the flexibility to combine elements from multiple applications as necessary and then organize your material for more effective delivery." 
<p>
In addition, because Acrobat Player displays files in Adobe's resolution-independent PDF format, MediaExpress provides compatibility with all computer platforms regardless of application, resolution, or fonts.  Any projector equipped with MediaExpress always projects images at the best possible resolution, and preserves the integrity of your design, including formatting and positioning true to the original documents. 
<p>
Because Adobe Acrobat software uses a variety of compression technologies to reduce file size, users have the ability to share visually rich information in a very compact form--up to 400 simple text slides on one floppy disk!  PDF thus provides a convenient means of storing, transporting and sharing information.   
<p>
<B>Expanding the Market</B>
<p>
Because it removes the fears many people have of making an electronic presentation, MediaExpress will help to expand the market for desktop projection products.  As Hicks pointed out, the use of electronic presentations is still in the early adopter phase.  
<p>
"Fear of technology limits a huge number of people from taking advantage of this technology," he said.  "With its numerous cables and switches, they perceive that it's too complex, that they won't be able to set it up or operate it, or that the system will fail and they won't know how to fix it."
<p>
This helps to explain the figures released by Pacific Media Associates of Mountain View Calif., which show that the install base of presentation-creation software versus projectors is more than 25:1.  As Hicks noted, "that leaves a huge range of potential users who are comfortable authoring on a PC or Mac, but who are not comfortable hooking the devices up to another machine to share information with a group."  
<p>
<B>New and Existing Users</B>
<p>
With its unprecedented ease of use, bullet-proof reliability, ability to project images of the highest quality and increased content flexibility, MediaExpress is intended for both new and existing users.  "Because it's faster and better, new users will find it irresistible," said Hicks.  "And it's so easy current users will quickly convert."  
<p>
As a result, Hicks said <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Desktop Projectors equipped with MediaEpress will be used as multi-department, multi-user systems in a wide range of applications.  These include business and sales presentations, software demonstrations, education and training, interactive workgroup meetings and mobile presentations.  
<p>
Users who aren't comfortable setting up equipment, or who prefer not to use a laptop during a presentation, will find MediaExpress the perfect solution, as will anyone with a fixed message to communicate.  Moreover, the speed with which the system can be set up, as well as its worry-free reliability, will make it an invaluable asset to both frequent and occasional presenters.
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> MediaExpress system will begin shipping late May as an option available on all models of the Desktop Projector 4100.  Prices are as follows:  Floppy only (ME40F):  $1,495; Floppy with hard drive (ME40H):  $1,995.  All prices are U.S. suggested retail.
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corp. is a leader in desktop projection for large-screen, interactive presentations and workgroup sessions.  Headquartered in San Diego, Calif., the company designs, manufactures and markets a full line of award-winning LCD projection panels, LCD projectors and interactive presentation control systems.
<p>

<center>     #  #  #    </center>

<p>
Adobe and Acrobat are registered trademarks of Adobe Systems Incorporated.  Acrobat Player and Acrobat Exchange are trademarks of Adobe Systems Incorporated.
<br>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a registered trademark of Proxima Corporation.  Desktop Projection, Desktop Projector and MediaExpress are trademarks of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation.
