<HEAD>
<TITLE>New Desktop Projector 2910 features 650 ANSI Lumens</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_releases.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/press_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Press Releases"></A>
<H2><font color = "FF0000">PROXIMA</font> CORPORATION INTRODUCES<br>INDUSTRY'S BRIGHTEST LCD MULTIMEDIA PROJECTOR</H2>
<H3>New Desktop Projector 2910 features 650 ANSI Lumens</H3>
</center>

SAN DIEGO -- (May 8, 1996) -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM), a leader in projection technology, today announced the introduction of the <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP2910&sction=Description">Desktop Projector 2910</A> -- the industry's brightest LCD multimedia projector.  The new projector provides accurate, high-quality projection of computer and video images rated at an unprecedented 650 ANSI lumens, according to Michael Chaffin, <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> chief operating officer.  This extraordinary brightness fulfills long-standing market requirements for clear projection in presentations to large audiences and in high ambient light environments.
<p>
The newest member of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> award-winning Desktop Projector product line, the DP2910 is an enhanced version of the DP2900 projector.  The new model offers refinements in uniformity and consistency, and also provides a more efficient cooling system and quieter operation.  Connected to a PC-compatible or Macintosh computer, the DP2910 projects clear, brilliant images at VGA resolution (640-by-480 dpi) in 2 million colors from a palette of 16.7 million colors.  It can also display most SGVA images (800-by-600 dpi) in a windowed view.
<p>
"The DP2910 effectively establishes a new image brightness standard for LCD multimedia projectors," Chaffin said.  "With this projector, presenters can deliver dynamic computer-based presentations without darkening the room, allowing them to maintain the eye contact with their audiences that is so vital to the overall impact of their communications."
<p>
The DP2910 weighs just over 22 pounds, and incorporates advanced ergonomics and a compact design that offers virtually the same user-friendly interface as a standard desktop computer peripheral.  In addition, it includes a stereo audio output system and state-of-the-art digital video controller that projects exceptionally sharp, uniform video images in all three international video standards (NTSC, PAL, and SECAM), as well as S-VHS.
<p>
By adding <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> optional <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=DP2060/2050&sction=Description">Cyclops&#174;</A> interactive pointer system, which functions as a cordless mouse, users essentially have a complete, all-in-one desktop projection solution.  "With Cyclops, presenters can pull down menus, open files, and perform other interactive  tasks from up to 40 feet away from their computer," said Chaffin.
<p>
The DP2910 is designed to meet the needs of corporate and individual users in both presentation and workgroup applications.  In addition to being ideal for use in larger conference rooms under challenging light conditions, the compact, light-weight projector fits easily into an airplane overhead luggage compartment.  "It's the perfect tool for traveling executives, field sales people, corporate presenters and trainers in a variety of industries, as well as educators and government professionals," Chaffin said.
<p>
Available through <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> authorized resellers, the DP2910 sells for a suggested retail price of $7,995 U.S.  For more information please contact Proxima Corporation at 619/457-5500.
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of Desktop Projection products that bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.  The company's headquarters are in San Diego, California.
<p>

<center>     #  #  #    </center>

<p>
Desktop Projector and Cyclops are trademarks of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation. All other trademarks and registered trademarks are the property of their respective owners.
<p>
This press release contains forward-looking statements relating to new products.  Actual results could differ materially from those projected in the forward-looking statements.  Certain risk factors (such as those relating to short product lives, technological change, competition and pricing pressures) could materially affect the projections.  Investors are strongly encouraged to review the risk factors set forth in <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> last filed Forms 10-K and 10-Q.
<p>

