<HEAD>
<TITLE>Joint Product Development Effort with Prolux Corporation</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_releases.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/press_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Press Releases"></A>
<H2><font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation Announces Joint Product<br> Development Effort with Prolux Corporation</H2>
<H3>Alliance to Produce Advanced Technology Multimedia Projectors</H3>
</center>

San Diego, California, May 2, 1996 . . . <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM) today announced its entry into a joint product development effort with Prolux Corporation, a leading designer of advanced technology LCD-based illumination systems.  The two companies will combine their individual design expertise to produce a compact multimedia projector   
that is optimized for large audience presentations or high ambient light   
environments.
<p>
"By undertaking a joint development effort with an acknowledged LCD   
illumination technology expert like Prolux, we'll be able to bring a high   
brightness multimedia projector to market in a much shorter period of time," said John E. Rehfeld, president and CEO of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font>.   "This will allow us to more quickly expand our product line to penetrate the rapidly growing market for multimedia projectors designed for larger audiences," he added.
<p>
According to Taylor Fletcher, president of Prolux Corporation, "we are   
delighted to be involved in a co-development effort with an established   
industry leader like <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font>, and view their decision to work with us as a significant statement regarding the performance and quality of our LCD illumination systems.  We look forward to working closely with <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> to produce a multimedia projector that provides unparalleled levels of brightness and clarity."
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of desktop projection products which bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.
<p>

<center>     #  #  #    </center>

<p>
This press release contains forward-looking statements relating to new   
products.  Actual results could differ materially from those projected in   
the forward-looking statements.  Certain risk factors (such as those   
relating to short product lives, technological change and technical   
difficulties with new products, competition and pricing pressures) could   
materially affect the projections.  Investors are strongly encouraged to   
review the risk factors set forth in <font color = "FF0000">Proxima's</font> last filed Forms 10-K and   
10-Q.
<p>
