<HEAD>
<TITLE>Financial Information - Proxima Corporation Named In Lawsuit</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="about_financial.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/financial_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Financial Information"></A>
<br>
<table width = 100%>
	<tr>
		<td align = right>For more information contact:<br>
Todd Savitt, Investor Relations<br>
(619) 457-5500 x1208<br></td>
	</tr>
</table>
<p>
<font size = +2><font color = "FF0000">PROXIMA</font> CORPORATION NAMED IN LAWSUIT</font>
<p>
</center>

<font size = "+1">San Diego, California,  August 19, 1996 -- <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM) announced today that it has been named as a defendant in a lawsuit filed in U.S. District Court for the Southern District of California and in another lawsuit filed in Superior Court of California, County of San Diego, alleging that the company made false or misleading statements of material facts in public disclosures.
<p>
"We believe that these suits are without merit and we intend to defend the suits vigorously," said chief financial officer Dennis Whittler.  <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of multimedia projection products that bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.  The company's headquarters are in San Diego, California.</font>
