<HEAD>
<TITLE>Financial Information - 1996 Third Quarter Results</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="about_financial.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/financial_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "Financial Information"></A>
<p>
<font size = +2><font color = "FF0000">PROXIMA</font> CORPORATION REPORTS RECORD
<br>
REVENUE FOR THIRD QUARTER OF FISCAL 1996</font>
</center>

<p>
<font size = "+1">
<B>Record order rates and record backlog were attained</B>
<p>
San Diego, California, January 22, 1996 . . . <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation (NASDAQ:PRXM) today reported net income of $3,229,000 , or 46 cents per share, for the three months ended December 31, 1995, compared to net income of $3,879,000, or 55 cents per share, in the same period last   
year.  Revenue for the quarter increased to $44,216,000 from $36,240,000   
in the third quarter of fiscal 1995.
<p>
 For the first nine months of fiscal 1996, net income was $6,232,000, or   
89 cents per share, on revenues of $112,206,000 compared to $9,179,000,   
or $1.35 per share, on revenues of $95,004,000 during the same period of   
fiscal 1995.
<p>
 "We are pleased with the results and the progress that we have made in   
the third quarter," said Kenneth E. Olson, chairman and CEO of <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font>.   "While revenues early in the quarter were slow due to the unavailability of key components, we were able to solve the major component issues by the end of December.  Both the Desktop Projector 2810 and the DP5100 were shipped in record quantities."
<p>
 "The overall market for high-brightness desktop projectors continued to   
expand rapidly during the quarter," noted Olson.  "The market's response   
to our new line of  high-brightness Desktop Projectors has been   
exceptional as evidenced by record order rates and backlog levels."    
<p>
<font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation is a leading developer, manufacturer and marketer of desktop projection products which bring the power of the computer to the workgroup.  These systems increase the productivity and effectiveness of business meetings, interactive workgroup sessions, training, and computer-based presentations.
</font>
