<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>"Win with Proxima!" Winning Proposals</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="univ_entries.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/school_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Back To School"></A>
<p>
<H2>"Win With Proxima!" Winning Proposals</H2>
</center>

<br>
<table>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><font size = "+2"><B>First Prize:</B> </td>
		<td><font size = "+2">Lucie Podd<br>North Country Union High School, Newport, VT</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<p>

<center>
<font size = "+1">
<font color = "CF0000"><B>Electronic Publishing - A Vehicle for Leadership & Technology</B></font>
<p>
</center>

<IMG SRC="gifs/lucie.gif" width = 158 height = 216 align = right hspace = 6 alt = "Photo of Lucie Podd">
<B>Description/Objectives</B>
<p>
Business education teacher Lucie Podd has proposed to include a new "Electronic Publishing" course as part of the business education curriculum at North Country Union High School in Newport, Vermont.  The course will utilize and instruct students on the use of multimedia applications and equipment.  The student objectives are as follows:  
<p>
<menu>
-	Improve communication skills; <br>
-	Develop leadership skills;  <br>
-	Learn to use new technologies; <br>
-	Instruct staff from other disciplines about the power of using desktop projection units and multimedia to transform and enhance instruction; <br>
-	Introduce the local community to the effectiveness of combining desktop projection equipment with multimedia.
</menu>
<p>
<B>Implementation</B>
<p>
The course will be implemented through the business education department to second year students who have already learned to touch type, use Windows-based word processing, spreadsheets, databases, and telecommunication.
<p>
Stage 1:  Training.  Utilize the desktop projector to facilitate training students on the tools.
<p>
Stage 2: Teaming Up/Selecting Projects.  Each student will be responsible for creating three multimedia projects, while collaborating with members from different areas of the school or local community.  Projects must have a useful purpose as a completed work, and must introduce others to the power of multimedia in the communication process (written and oral).
<p>
<menu>
Project 1:  Create a web page representing one facet of the <A HREF="http://www.together.net/~vtbused/ncu.htm">educational community</A>;
<p>
Project 2:  Create a web page representing one facet of the <A HREF="http://cyberfair.gsn.org/ncuhs/intro.htm">local community</A>;
<p>
Project 3:  Assist one teacher in the creating of a multimedia presentation to enhance instruction.
</menu>
<p>
Stage 3:  Use the available technology, local resources, and teamwork to complete the projects.  Collaboration will insure consistency, and students will learn to recognize, appreciate and use each others' strengths for improved results.  Leadership skills will be developed as they collaborate with others outside the classroom.  Desktop projection equipment used to communicate their vision.
<p>
Stage 4:  Presentations to community groups (Rotary Club, etc.), academic departments, groups within the school, and elementary schools.  
<p>
Stage 5:  Measurement & Assessment.  A pre-and post-project assessment tool will be developed to measure the increase in students' technical and communication skills.  Success measurement will be through self-evaluation, peer evaluation and teacher evaluation. The impact on the school and community will be measured by the number of students, staff, and community members introduced to multimedia throughout the year.
<p>
<B>Technology Model</B>
<p>
The business education classroom lab includes 20 networked IBM-compatible computers, a laser and dot matrix printers, a flatbed color scanner, a still video capture tool, and QuickCam.  Five of the computer stations are connected to the Internet.  All computers have Microsoft Office and Internet Assistant loaded.  Some are equipped with Corel Draw and Hyperstudio.  The addition of Proxima's mobile media center will greatly enhance the model's capability.</font>
<p>
<br>

<center>
