<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The New MediaExpress Image Display System!</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="hot_products.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/new_products_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP  border = none alt = "New Products"></A>
<p>
<H2>MediaExpress lets you concentrate on <br>
your message instead of your method.</H2>
</center>

<IMG SRC="gifs/medex.gif" align = right width = 285 height = 191 hspace = 5>
<font size = "+2"><B>T</B></font><font size = "+1">he MediaExpress image display system adds yet another valuable feature to your <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font>&#174; Desktop Projector. <A HREF="../Solutions/proxima.cgi?template=item.html&item=MediaExpress&sction=Description">MediaExpress</A> makes it easy to deliver electronic presentations, without the computer, the cables, or the worry.
Creating a presentation with MediaExpress is easy. Use your favorite presentation software program to create electronic slides. Save them to a PC-formatted floppy disk and insert the disk into the MediaExpress drive in your Desktop Projector. Now you're ready to start the show.
<p>
MediaExpress "plays" your images without any complicated setup. Use the forward and reverse keys on the included Cyclops&#174; remote to control your presentation. It's that easy. Use MediaExpress to make your ideas look good, without worrying about all of the things that can go wrong.
<p>
<B>Based on the industry standard for sharing documents</B> 
<p>
<IMG SRC="gifs/media_logo.gif" align = left width = 180 height = 28 hspace = 6>One of the truly remarkable features of MediaExpress is that it's based on Adobe&#174; Acrobat&#174; and Portable Document Format (PDF)-the standard for sharing electronic information internally and across the World Wide Web.
<p>
<A HREF="frame_adobe2.html"><IMG SRC="gifs/acrobat_logo.gif" align = right border = none width = 88 height = 31 hspace = 6></A>Use the <A HREF="frame_adobe2.html">Adobe Acrobat software</A>  that comes with your MediaExpress to quickly and easily create PDF files on your PC or Macintosh. Simply select the Adobe Acrobat PDF Writer as your printer and print. When MediaExpress "plays back" the PDF file, it looks just like your original-whether it's a spreadsheet, a presentation, or any other electronic document.
<p>
<center>
<table border = 4>
	<tr>
		<td align = center><font size = "+1">&#160Download a <A HREF="medex.pdf"><IMG SRC="gifs/pdf_logo.gif" width = 28 height = 31 border = none></A> file of the new <A HREF="medex.pdf">MediaExpress datasheet</A>! </td>
	</tr>
</table>
</center>
<p>
<A HREF="frame_adobe1.html"><IMG SRC="gifs/adobe_logo.gif" align = left border = none width = 92 height = 72 hspace = 4></A><A HREF="frame_adobe1.html">Adobe Acrobat</A> allows you to gather content from any platform, because it supports PC, Macintosh, and UNIX systems and PostScript files. Adobe Acrobat and MediaExpress make it easy for you to present information from any computer system, your company's network, or even the Internet.
<p>
<B>Powerful and easy to use</B> 
<p>
MediaExpress is simple to use, allowing you to concentrate on your message instead of your computer. But it doesn't economize on power or flexibility. MediaExpress has everything you need to handle high impact presentations with ease.
<p>
MediaExpress includes Adobe Acrobat Exchange software for your computer that enables you to add transition effects, create links between pages, and combine images from different applications or computer platforms. When your presentation is loaded into MediaExpress, you can hide pages and modify transition effects directly from your Desktop Projector-without ever having to go back to your computer.
<p>
Your presentation will always look its best-whether you're using a high-resolution XGA projector or a more typical VGA model. MediaExpress displays at the exact resolution that you need. You can also use MediaExpress to zoom in on your image, highlighting important parts of your presentation with exact detail.
<p>
<B>Reliable and worry-free</B>
<p>
Not only does MediaExpress deliver the best quality, it delivers reliability. Any PDF file plays in any MediaExpress-and it works every time. For simple electronic presentations, MediaExpress gives you the power and flexibility to express your ideas without struggling with a computer. It's the complete, self-contained, image display solution. 
<p>
<B>Features</B>
<p>
<UL>
<LI>Transforms Desktop Projector into self-contained, image display system with no cables to connect
<LI>Uses Adobe Acrobat Player for sharing and displaying information
<LI>Simple, intuitive controls make it easy to use
<LI>Resolution independent, so images always look their best
<LI>Displays electronic slides from any application or computer so that there are no new applications to learn
<LI>Supports simple sequential slide shows or adds links, zoom, and special effects for greater impact
<LI>Allows integration of slides from your desktop, network, or World Wide Web sites
<LI>Uses inexpensive 3.5-inch disks for data transfer and storage
<LI>Optional hard drive allows storage of multiple presentations inside the projector
<LI>Supports the Cyclops interactive pointer system for precise point-and-click control of your projected image
</UL>
<B>MediaExpress turns your Desktop Projector into a self-contained, electronic presentation system.</B>
<p>
With MediaExpress your <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Desktop Projector can operate totally independent of your computer. This means that your <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Desktop Projector does not need to be connected to your computer when you are creating or giving a presentation.
</font>
<p>

<hr width = 300>

<p>
MediaExpress incorporates Adobe&#174; Acrobat&#174; Player technology. This technology was developed by Adobe Systems Incorporated and was licensed to <font color = "FF0000">Proxima</font> Corporation in an agreement made public in May 1995.
<p>
