<HEAD>
<TITLE> Proxima Allows Teachers and Students to Project the Classroom of the   
Future </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="univ_app.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/school_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Back To School"></A>
<p>
<H2>Educational Applications of Proxima Products</H2>
</center>

<font size = "+1">Marie Colalucci<br>
Director of Business/Computer Education,<br>
Farmingdale Public Schools District</font>
<p>

<center>
<H3><font color = "CF0000">Proxima Allows Teachers and Students to Project<br>the Classroom of the Future</font></H3>
</center>

<table width = 596>
	<tr>
		<td valign = top><font size = "+1">In the Farmingdale Public Schools District, teachers and students alike are making impressive presentations, thanks to the Proxima Desktop Projector 2750.
<p>
While teachers are discovering what a useful instructional tool the Desktop Projector is, students as young as fourth grade are learning to share information with their classmates in a whole new way.  According to Marie Colalucci, Director of Business/Computer Education, "The students experiment with a lot of different software programs, like LinkWay and   
HyperStudio for Windows.  With the Desktop Projector, they can share   
the content of their work not only with their teachers but with their fellow students.  It's a much more interactive process."
<p>
Colalucci further stated that among teachers, one of the most popular uses for the Desktop Projector is to display student portfolios which are bibliographies of their best work from the year.
<p>
Although the district has used LCD projection equipment in the past, images literally paled in comparison to the Desktop Projector's.  "The old LCD panels couldn't handle the enormous number of colors our Desktop Projector displays.  Nor could they support video.  They were sufficient for text-only demonstrations, and that was about it," Colalucci said.  By contrast, the Desktop Projector has full multimedia capabilities.  "We hook it up to CD-ROMs and laser discs, so it allows us to take advantage of the wealth of multimedia instructional materials available.  The images are phenomenal!"</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<p>
<br>

<center>
[&#160 <A HREF="../university.html">Presenters University</A>&#160 |&#160 
<A HREF="../../Solving/solving.html">Support And Service</A>&#160 |&#160 
