<HEAD>
<TITLE>Improving Communication and Problem Solving Skills</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="FFFFFF" vlink="AF0040" alink="04BC04">

<center>
<A HREF="univ_app.map"><IMG SRC="gifs/school_header.gif" width = 600 height = 114  ISMAP border = none alt = "Back To School"></A>
<p>
<H2>Educational Applications of Proxima Products</H2>
</center>

<br>
<font size = "+2">Carol Martin<br>
6th Grade Teacher<br>
Billing R-IV School</font>
<p>

<center>
<font size = "+1">
<font color = "CF0000"><B>Improving Communication and Problem Solving Skills</B></font>
<p>
</center>

The objective of my "Win with Proxima" plan is to improve the communication
and problem solving skills of fifth and sixth grade language arts students. I will use a digital camera, computer and Proxima projector to improve writing skills, to create a class journal for historical and demonstration purposes, and to motivate students to communicate more effectively. Photographs of students, sites and situations will be displayed via our Proxima Desktop Projector. They can be cropped, enhanced or even shown in cartoon form. Student responses to the photographs will be typed in, revised and group edited. Pictures can be shown to an entire class, and text will be seen almost as soon as it is spoken. No more waiting for responses to be written on the chalkboard! It will create writing prompts which will motivate visual, oral and written communication. Each day's journal entry can be stored for further revision after students have had time for reflection. It will eventually be printed and bound into book form with our spiral binding machine for placement in our school media center. The combination of digital camera and Proxima media center will create a positive learning environment.
<p>
The effectiveness of the program will be assessed by teacher-directed writing samples using a teacher-made rubric to measure: (1) responding to a
writing prompt, (2) using a variety of descriptive language, (3) using standard grammar, mechanics and spelling, and (4) expressing individual ideas. A pretest and posttest will be given. It will also be evaluated by a student opinion survey and by the final product of the class journal.</font>
</menu>
<p>
<br>

