<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">
  <TITLE>Context Institute's Great Transition of '96</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>The Great Transition of '96</H1>

<P><BR>
Wondering why <I>IN CONTEXT</I> is no longer in print? Here's the story
...</P>

<P>The period between November 1995 and September 1996 has been the most
tumultuous in Context Institute's 17 year history. During that period we've:
</P>

<UL>
  <LI>had a sever financial crisis </LI>
  <LI>been engrossed in an long conflict over Context Institute (CI) and
  its assets, including <I>IN CONTEXT</I> (IC) </LI>
  <LI>changed the medium for publishing IC from print to the web. </LI>
</UL>

<P><BR>
If you want to know more about what's happened, our thinking about moving
from print to the web, and/or have questions/comments to make about this
transition, please read on:<BR>
<BR>
1) In the second half of September we sent letters to the <I>IN CONTEXT</I>
subscriber list dealing with the main points of this transition. Here are
the letters: </P>

<UL>
  <LI><A HREF="altr.htm">Ann Medlock's letter</A> (for the CI Board) describing
  the organizational crisis of the past year. </LI>
  <LI><A HREF="rltr.htm">Robert Gilman's letter</A> describing what's happening
  with IC on the web. </LI>
</UL>

<P><BR>
2) We couldn't cover everything in those letters. For a fuller picture,
we'll develop a Frequently Asked Questions page about the transition. Send
your questions to <A HREF="mailto:ci@context.org">ci@context.org</A><BR>
<BR>
3) We will also develop a page of Reader Responses. Send your comments also
to <A HREF="mailto:ci@context.org">ci@context.org</A> </P>

<P><HR><A HREF="../../ICLIB/permiss.htm">All contents copyright (c)1996
by Context Institute, all rights reserved.</A><BR>
<BR>
Please send comments to <A HREF="mailto:webmaster@context.org">webmaster@context.org<BR>
</A><BR>
<I>Last Updated 4 October 1996</I>. <BR>
<BR>
URL: http://www.context.org/GROUPS/CI/trans96.htm<BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="../../index.html">Home</A><BR>
</BODY>
