<HEAD>
  <TITLE>Affinity Long Distance Service</TITLE>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="../IMAGES/Affin.5.gif" WIDTH="448" HEIGHT="48"
ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B><I><FONT SIZE=+2>Long Distance Savings With A Purpose<BR>
</FONT></I></B></P>

<H3>With Context Institute's Affinity program you can simultaneously:</H3>

<UL>
  <LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Get a guaranteed <B>10% saving</B> over your current
  long distance service, <I>no matter what plan you currently use</I>. AND<BR>
  </FONT></LI>
  <LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Support this web site at <B><I>no</I></B>&nbsp; cost
  to you</FONT>. </LI>
</UL>

<P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>To just do it</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+1>, call <B>1-800-670-0008</B>.
Be sure to give them the Context Institute organization number <B>#971026-000</B>.
</FONT>Call now or write BOTH numbers down so you'll have them handy when
you do call.</P>

<P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>To find out more</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+1>, read on :</FONT></P>

<UL>
  <LI>What is <B><A HREF="#what">Affinity</A></B>? </LI>
  <LI>What are the program benefits for <B><A HREF="#benefits">residential</A></B>
  phone service? </LI>
  <LI>What are the program benefits for <B><A HREF="#busbenefits">business</A></B>
  phone service? </LI>
  <LI>Why is Context Institute <B><A HREF="#whyci">working with</A></B> Affinity?
  </LI>
  <LI>What has been the <B><A HREF="#experience">experience</A></B> with
  Affinity? </LI>
  <LI>Can my <B><A HREF="#orgwork">organization</A></B> also work with Affinity?
  </LI>
  <LI>The details. </LI>
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>... or just call us at 360/221-6044<BR>
</FONT><BR>
<HR><BR>
</P>

<H3><A NAME="what"></A>WHAT IS AFFINITY?</H3>

<P>Affinity is a company, started in 1990, that provides long distance phone
service in cooperation with professional associations and non-profit organizations
(like Context Institute). Affinity uses one of the most advanced telecommunications
network in America (currently MCI), but, as a fully independent company,
provides its own customer service and billing. It buys large blocks of phone
service at a significant discount and passes the savings on to its customers
(10% for residential service) and to the cooperating organizations (an additional
5%). <BR>
<BR>
Affinity also does not advertise, and <I>the money it saves by not advertising
is the real reason it can offer such significant savings</I>.<BR>
<BR>
By signing up with Affinity, you are simply redirecting part of your phone
bill (which now goes to the advertizing budget of your present long distance
carrier) back into your wallet and into the support of Context Institute
and this web site. You save, CI thrives. It's a real win-win!<BR>
</P>

<H3><A NAME="benefits"></A>PROGRAM BENEFITS FOR <A HREF="#resorbus">RESIDENTIAL</A>
SERVICE</H3>

<UL>
  <LI>10% <A HREF="#gsp">GUARANTEED SAVINGS</A> over your current plan <I>no
  matter what it is.</I> (For example, if AT&amp;T is saving you 25%, Affinity
  will save you an <I>additional</I> 10% over what AT&amp;T gives you.) </LI>
  <LI><A HREF="#sixsec">Six-second incremental billing</A>. (Other companies
  round your calls to the next full minute.) </LI>
  <LI>Easy 1-plus dialing for all calls (just like the &quot;Big 3&quot;).
  No special codes to use or memorize. </LI>
  <LI>Free <A HREF="#travelcards">Affinity Travel Card</A>(s) (saving you
  as much as 50% in surcharges). </LI>
  <LI><A HREF="#compbill">Comparative bill</A> clearly outlining the savings
  you have received over your previous plan. </LI>
  <LI>A <A HREF="#giftcert">Gift Certificate</A> from Affinity to help offset
  any switch-over fees. </LI>
</UL>

<P>It's easy to switch to Affinity; just call <B>1-800-670-0008</B>, 7 am
through 11 pm Central Time. <B>Be sure to give them the Context Institute
organization number #971026-000.</B> Call right now, or write both numbers
down so that you'll have them handy when you do call.<BR>
<BR>
Or, if you like, you can fill in a <A HREF="afresins.htm">Residential Service
Request</A> form and send it to us.<BR>
<BR>
If you have any questions, just call us at 360/221-6044.<BR>
</P>

<H3><A NAME="busbenefits"></A>PROGRAM BENEFITS FOR <A HREF="#resorbus">BUSINESS</A>
SERVICE</H3>

<P>Business customers currently using AT&amp;T, MCI or Sprint switched access
service will receive the following discounts depending on volume usage per
month: <BR>
</P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P>$0 to $500 -- 20% savings<BR>
  $500 to $1,000 -- 15% savings<BR>
  $1,000 to $2,500 -- 10% savings<BR>
  Over $2,500 -- 5% savings<BR>
  </P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P>Business customers now using a &quot;Non-Big 3&quot; carrier program
will receive a 5% savings. All these savings are guaranteed.<BR>
<BR>
Like residential customers, business customers get easy 1-plus dialing for
all calls, <A HREF="#sixsec">six-second incremental billing</A>, free <A
HREF="#travelcards">travel cards</A>, and the finest fiber optic, digital
network.<BR>
<BR>
Affinity offers business users enhanced telecommunications services, including
<A HREF="#busbill">detailed billing</A>, <A HREF="#accncodes">accounting
codes</A>, and <A HREF="#800service">800 service</A>.<BR>
<BR>
It's easy to switch your business long distance service to Affinity; just
call 1-800-670-0008, 7 am through 11 pm Central Time. <B>Be sure to give
the Context Institute organization number #971026-000.</B> Write it down
now with the 800 number so that you'll have it handy when you call.<BR>
<BR>
Or, if you like, just call us at 360/221-6044.<BR>
</P>

<H3><A NAME="whyci"></A>WHY IS CONTEXT INSTITUTE WORKING WITH AFFINITY?</H3>

<P>For years we've been looking for ways to fund the transition to a more
sustainable culture by:<BR>
</P>

<UL>
  <LI>introducing more efficient practices that could reduce waste and save
  money, and </LI>
  <LI>using some of that saved money to support the cultural transformation
  process. </LI>
</UL>

<P>We've been inspired by the example of &quot;energy service companies.&quot;
These companies find businesses that are using energy inefficiently, offer
to upgrade the business's equipment for no initial cost, and get paid by
sharing a portion of the savings (typically 50% of the savings over five
years). We've written about generalizing the energy service company example
in a number of recent issues, including &quot;<A HREF="ICLIB/IC33/Gilman.htm">Building
The Movement</A>&quot; (page 56,<I> IC</I> #33) and &quot;<A HREF="ICLIB/IC36/Gilman2.htm">Looking
Back From 2003</A>&quot; (page 56, <I>IC </I>#36).<BR>
<BR>
We were thus quite intrigued when we discovered the Affinity program and
realized that it had put this principle into practice. Clearly, it is only
a small step, but it is a step in the right direction -- and it works!<BR>
</P>

<H3><A NAME="experience"></A>OUR EXPERIENCE WITH AFFINITY</H3>

<P>It's been great! Over 200 people (and businesses!) have signed up with
Affinity through Context Institute since we started offering this service
in 1993 -- and of course we use it ourselves. After years of use we can't
see any downside (unless you <I>really</I> want to support AT&amp;T's or
MCI's or Sprint's advertizing budget!).<BR>
<BR>
The financial support is, of course, very welcome. (Affinity donates 5%
of each member's phone bill to Context Institute -- with no extra cost to
the member.) However, we wouldn't do this if it weren't fundamentally a
good, innovative program. It is.</P>

<P>To read what others have to say about the service, click <A HREF="#moreexperience">here</A>.<BR>
</P>

<H3><A NAME="orgwork"></A>CAN MY ORGANIZATION ALSO WORK WITH AFFINITY?</H3>

<P>Yes. Just get in touch with us and we'll be glad to help you get started
as we have for several other organizations. You can <A HREF="mailto:dgilman@context.org">email</A>
us or call us at 360/221-6044.<BR>
</P>

<H3>THE DETAILS</H3>

<P><A NAME="resorbus"></A><B><I>How can I tell if my phone service is &quot;residential&quot;
or &quot;business&quot;?</I></B><BR>
<BR>
Affinity bases its &quot;rates&quot; against those that you are currently
using. Your present long distance calling plan determines what &quot;type&quot;
of customer you will become in the Affinity system. Therefore if your current
calling plan is a residential plan then you will become an Affinity Residential
Customer. If you are currently using a plan that was designed for business,
then you will become a business customer. Unlike the local telephone company,
it does not matter where or how you use your service. It's your current
plan that will determine your rates, discounts and billing format once you
switch to Affinity.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="gsp"></A><B><I>The Affinity Guaranteed Savings Plan and <BR>
Double-Your-Money-Back Guarantee</I></B><BR>
<BR>
Affinity guarantees a minimum percentage savings (10% for residential customers;
5 - 20% for business customers, depending on volume) over any current program
you currently use. If you don't save the minimum percentage on your first
Affinity billing, Affinity will credit your account in full AND write you
a check for that amount, immediately! In addition, if within 90 days following
service activation you become dissatisfied for any reason, Affinity will
pay to switch you back to the carrier of your choice.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="sixsec"></A><B><I>Six-second incremental billing</I></B><BR>
<BR>
This simply means that you only pay for the time you use. Other carriers
round calls up to the next full minute, charging for time that isn't used.
After Affinity's 18-second first minute minimum, calls are billed at six-second
increments. Affinity measures it's minutes by tenths, so, if you make a
call for 2 minutes and 24 seconds, 2.4 minutes will appear on your bill.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="travelcards"></A><B><I>Affinity Travel Cards</I></B><BR>
<BR>
Affinity's Travel Card is one of the very few travel cards in America that
offers six-second incremental billing and bills at discounted rates. Affinity's
per-call surcharge is only 40&#162;. That's almost as much as a 50% savings
over other major carriers! Travel card features include:<BR>
</P>

<UL>
  <LI>Easy access, toll free calling from any phone in America </LI>
  <LI>Multiple call feature </LI>
  <LI>Mis-dial feature </LI>
  <LI>International Calling </LI>
</UL>

<P><A NAME="compbill"></A><B><I>Residential Comparison Billing</I></B><BR>
<BR>
Comparison Billing is an Affinity exclusive for those who previously used
one of the &quot;Big 3&quot; (AT&amp;T, MCI, or Sprint). Every month, call
by call, you see what you would have paid and what you are saving with Affinity.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="giftcert"></A><B><I>Gift Certificate</I></B><BR>
<BR>
Affinity sends you a Gift Certificate for $5 for your first phone line,
plus $3 for any additional lines. You fill out the certificate, return it
with your first Affinity payment, and a credit will be made to your account.
This credit helps to offset any switch fees that your local telephone company
may charge to switch your long distance carrier.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="busbill"></A><B><I>Business Billing</I></B><BR>
<BR>
Affinity's business billing format offers detailed easy-to-read summaries
for increased managment efficiency. Area code patterns, type of call detail,
and long-call analysis are just a few of the summaries provided, and it's
all standard. There is no extra charge.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="accncodes"></A><B><I>Enhanced Accounting Codes</I></B><BR>
<BR>
This is an optional service available to business customers. Accounting
codes are 2 to 7 digits dialed at the end of a called number to categorize
communication expenses. Your choice of validated or non-validated codes
provide a simple, effective way to identify calls made by a pre-determined
employee, project, client, department or other accounting category. There
is a nominal monthly charge, currently $5 for each location.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="800service"></A><B><I>800 Service</I></B><BR>
<BR>
Affinity offers a quality, flexible, 800 service. It works over your regular
business line and can be customized to fit your special needs - from improving
customer relations to increasing profitability. Affinity 800 is billed in
<A HREF="#sixsec">six-second increments</A> - and our rates are guaranteed
to beat your current plan. Affinity 800 service can be international in
scope or limited to an area code, if so desired. There is a nominal monthly
charge for each 800 number. </P>

<P><A NAME="moreexperience"></A><B><I>More Experience</I></B></P>

<P>&quot;The best compliment I can pay you is to say there is no difference
between the service of AT&amp;T, MCI, Sprint and Affinity. Affinity is better
though, because I'm paying a lot less. I'm thrilled with these rates!&quot;
<I>Julia Griewank, Rochester, NH</I></P>

<P>&quot;Westfield residents and businesses received the promised savings,
and we get royalty checks in a timely manner. Affinity has become one of
our most important fundraisers.&quot; <BR>
<I>Joseph McGovern, Executive Director, Boys &amp; Girls Club of Greater
Westfield</I></P>

<P>&quot;Our members are happy with the low rates available through the
Affinity program, and the services have been excellent. As we sign up new
subscribers, our income check from Affinity continues to grow. We've been
trying to figure out the downside to this program -- and we still haven't
found one.&quot; <I>Henry Hanson, Deputy Director, Iowa Trial Lawyers Association</I><BR>
<BR>
