<HEAD>
    <TITLE>CI Books</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<B><I>EcoTeam Workbook </I></B><BR>
In 1990, in collaboration with the Global Action Plan for the Earth, <A HREF="ci.htm">Context
Institute</A> formulated the goals which became the official Earth Day 1990
&quot;Agenda for the Green Decade,&quot; then co-authored, designed, and
edited the <I>Household EcoTeam Workbook. </I>The workbook translates the
global goals into individual actions which small groups of homeowners and
tenants can implement over a six-month period to make their consumption
patterns - including energy and water use, solid waste, and transportation
- more environmentally sustainable. The workbook has been translated and
adapted for use in the Netherlands, Norway, Canada, Sweden, Great Britain,
Switzerland, and Germany. <B><I><BR>
<BR>
Eco-Village Report </I></B><BR>
In 1991, we completed a contract to survey eco-villages and sustainable
communities throughout the world, looking particularly for the kinds of
supporting services and programs that are helpful to developing communities.
We studied many key areas: leadership; communication of values; ownership
and economics; architectural design; energy, waste, and water; agriculture
and animal husbandry; recreation, the arts, and celebration. The study is
now available as a publication.<BR>
