<HEAD>
  <TITLE>Affinity Residential Service Request Instructions</TITLE>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="../IMAGES/Affin.25.gif" WIDTH="224" HEIGHT="24" 
ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-1>Long Distance Savings With a Purpose</FONT></P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>RESIDENTIAL SERVICE REQUEST INSTRUCTIONS</H2>

<P>It's easy to sign up and get at least 10% savings over your current plan.
Just:<BR>
</P>

<UL>
  <LI>Fill in one of the accompanying forms </LI>
  <LI>Print it out </LI>
  <LI>Sign it </LI>
  <LI>Mail it to Context Institute, PO Box 946, Langley, WA 98260 </LI>
</UL>

<P>We'll take care of the rest!<BR>
<BR>
It is helpful to have a copy of your most recent bills from your present
local telephone company and long distance carrier on hand as you fill out
the form. Remember to fill in <B>all</B> the requested information. (The
Federal Communications Commission [FCC] and your local phone company are
fussy about these details to make sure your phone service doesn't get switched
unless <B>you</B> want it switched.) <BR>
<BR>
Now, choose a form:<BR>
</P>

<UL>
  <LI><A HREF="afresfrm.htm">On-line form</A>, to be filled out on your computer.
  (It will still need to be printed out for your signature, and then mailed.)
  </LI>
  <LI><A HREF="afrespap.htm">Paper form</A>, to be filled out by hand. (Use
  this if you have more than 3 telephone numbers or if you can't print out
  the On-line form on one page.) </LI>
</UL>

<P><HR><BR>
</P>

<H3>Detailed Instructions</H3>

<P>You probably won't need these, but they are here just in case you do.
You can get to them via links from the forms.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="name"></A><B><I>Name</I></B><BR>
<BR>
This needs to be the <I>name under which your phone number is listed</I>
with your local telephone company (also referred to as the LEC, Local Exchange
Carrier). Copy it directly from a recent phone bill. It must be EXACTLY
as shown on the bill -- even if there is an incorrect spelling. <BR>
<BR>
If the name doesn't make an EXACT match with the local phone company's records,
it may be rejected.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="physical"></A><B><I>Phone Location Address</I></B><BR>
<BR>
The local phone company always identifies you by the physical location (address)
of your phone service, not by the billing address. Again, if the local phone
company doesn't see the information match in their system, the switch may
not be complete. If your physical location address is the same as your billing
address, or if your phone bill gives both, copy this directly from a recent
bill.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="billing"></A><B><I>Billing Address</I></B><BR>
<BR>
If you want your billing <I>from Affinity</I> sent to an address different
from your Phone Location Address, put it here. For this it makes no difference
what billing address your local phone company uses. It's your choice.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="numbers"></A><B><I>Telephone Numbers</I></B><BR>
<BR>
List each phone number at the Phone Location Address as they were issued
from the local telephone company. Attach an additional list if necessary.
Do not list any phone numbers other than those at this location.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="carrier"></A><B><I>Present Long Distance Carrier</I></B><BR>
<BR>
The name of your present long distance carrier, such as AT&amp;T, MCI, or
Sprint.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="plans"></A><B><I>Current Discount Calling Plan(s)</I></B><BR>
<BR>
For example, &quot;Reach Out America&quot; (AT&amp;T) or &quot;Friends &amp;
Family&quot; (MCI). This must be the plan(s) that you are currently signed
up for as indicated on your current bill. <BR>
<BR>
